column1: :has_definition ""A mass of gas which is separated from its surroundings by either 1) a thin liquid layer or 2) a physical or compositional discontinuity.""@en .

,A bubble is a type of mass of gas and also a type of something that at least has part of some interface layer. It is defined as a mass of gas which is separated from its surroundings by either 1) a thin liquid layer or 2) a physical or compositional discontinuity.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001686,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An object which is composed primarily of an environmental material""@en .

,The mass of environmental material is identified as being equivalent to something that intersects an object and something that is at least composed primarily of some environmental material. Additionally, the mass of environmental material is categorized as a type of object as well as a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some environmental material. Furthermore, the mass of environmental material is defined as an object which is primarily composed of an environmental material.",4,True
:has_definition ""An mass of environmental material which is composed primarily of a solid environmental material""@en .

,The mass of solid material is defined as an amount of environmental material that is composed primarily of a solid environmental material. It is identified as being the same as something that intersects with both the mass of environmental material and something that is at least composed primarily of some solid environmental material. Additionally, the mass of solid material is categorized as a type of mass of environmental material and also as a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some solid environmental material.",4,True
:has_definition ""An object which is composed primarily of a fluid.""@en

,The mass of fluid is equivalent to the intersection of the mass of environmental material and entities that are composed primarily of materials that are either gaseous environmental material, liquid environmental material, or a combination of both. Additionally, the mass of fluid is categorized as a type of mass of environmental material and also as a type of entities that are primarily composed of materials which could be either gaseous environmental material, liquid environmental material, or both. Furthermore, the mass of fluid is defined as an object which is primarily composed of a fluid and is exactly synonymous with the term ""fluid mass.""",5,True
:has_definition ""An object which is composed primarily of a gas.""@en

,The mass of gas has the same properties as the intersection of the mass of fluid and something that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material. It is a type of mass of fluid and also a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some gaseous environmental material. The mass of gas is defined as an object which is composed primarily of a gas. Moreover, it has an exact synonym, gaseous mass.",5,True
:has_definition ""An object which is composed primarily of a liquid.""@en

,The mass of liquid is defined as an object which is composed primarily of a liquid and is exactly synonymous with liquid mass. It is identified as a type of mass of fluid and also as a type of entity that is at least composed primarily of some liquid environmental material. Furthermore, the mass of liquid is equivalent to the intersection of something that has the mass of fluid and something that is at least composed primarily of some liquid environmental material.",5,True

:has_definition ""An mass of environmental materials which has appreciable quantities of several individual materials, such that the removal of one would convert the mass into a different entity.""@en .

,The mass of compounded environmental materials is equivalent to something that is at the intersection of the mass of environmental material and something that comprises at least 2 environmental materials. Additionally, the mass of compounded environmental materials is categorized under the mass of environmental material. Furthermore, it is defined as a mass of environmental materials that contains significant quantities of several individual materials, such that removing one would transform the mass into a different entity.",3,True
:has_definition ""A bubble which is composed primarily of methane.""@en .

,A methane gas bubble is a type of bubble and something that is at least composed primarily of methane. It is defined as a bubble which is composed primarily of methane.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001693,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A material isosurface within which pressure is approximately constant.""@en .

,An isobaric surface is a type of material isosurface that is defined as a material isosurface within which pressure is approximately constant.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001694,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A material isosurface within which salinity is approximately constant.""@en .
,An isohaline surface is a type of material isosurface, defined as a material isosurface within which salinity is approximately constant.",2,True
:has_definition ""A material isosurface within which density is approximately constant.""@en .
,An isopycnal surface, which is a type of material isosurface, is defined as a material isosurface within which density is approximately constant.",2,True
:has_definition ""A material isosurface within which temperature is approximately constant.""@en .
,An isothermal surface, a type of material isosurface, is defined as a material isosurface within which the temperature is approximately constant.",2,True
:has_definition ""An isobaric surface that is part of an atmosphere.""@en .
,An atmospheric isobaric surface, which is a type of isobaric surface, is defined as an isobaric surface that is part of an atmosphere.",2,True
:has_definition ""A weather front which separates air masses of tropical and polar origin.""@en .

,The polar front is a type of weather front defined as a weather front that separates air masses of tropical and polar origin.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001701,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An environment which has a climate with continually high temperatures and with considerable precipitation, at least during part of the year.""@en .

,A tropical environment is defined as an environment that has a climate with continually high temperatures and considerable precipitation, at least during part of the year. It is a type of environmental system and also a type that possesses some tropical qualities. Additionally, a tropical environment is the same as the intersection of an environmental system and something that has at least some tropical quality.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environment which has a climate with warm temperatures and with meagre precipitation.""@en .

,A subtropical environment is an environmental system that intersects with entities that have at least some subtropical qualities. This means it is not only categorized under environmental systems but also under entities that possess subtropical characteristics. Additionally, a subtropical environment is defined as an environment that features a climate characterized by warm temperatures and minimal precipitation.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environment which is located in a part of an astronomical body subject to polar climatic conditions.""@en .

,The polar environment is defined as an environment which is located in a part of an astronomical body subject to polar climatic conditions. It is a type of environmental system and also a type of entity that possesses some polar quality. Moreover, the polar environment is the same as an intersection of an environmental system and an entity that at least has some polar quality.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environment which is located in a part of an astronomical body subject to subpolar climatic conditions.""@en .

,A subpolar environment is equivalent to an intersection between an environmental system and anything that possesses at least some subpolar qualities. It is classified as a type of environmental system and also as a type of entity that exhibits some subpolar characteristics. Furthermore, a subpolar environment is defined as an environment situated in a region of an astronomical body that experiences subpolar climatic conditions.",4,True
:has_definition ""An environment which is located in a part of an astronomical body subject to temperate climatic conditions.""@en .

,A temperate environment is defined as an environment located in a part of an astronomical body subject to temperate climatic conditions. This environment is the same as something that is an intersection of an environmental system and something that at least has some temperate quality. Additionally, a temperate environment is a type of environmental system and also a type of something that has at least some temperate quality.",4,True

:has_definition ""A weather front which is nonoccluded and  which moves in the direction of the warmer air mass it is adjacent to, such that colder air will occupy the site where warmer air was previously present.""@en .

,A cold front is a type of weather front defined as a nonoccluded weather front that moves in the direction of the warmer air mass it is adjacent to, resulting in colder air occupying the site previously held by warmer air.",2,True

:has_definition ""A weather front which is nonoccluded and which moves in the direction of the colder air mass it is adjacent to, such that warmer air will occupy the site where colder air was previously present.""@en .

,A warm front is a type of weather front that is nonoccluded and moves in the direction of the colder air mass adjacent to it. This movement results in warmer air occupying the site where colder air was previously present.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001708,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A weather front at which warm air is ascending to high altitudes along the frontal surface.""@en .

,An anafront is a type of weather front defined as a weather front at which warm air is ascending to high altitudes along the frontal surface.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001709,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A weather front at which warm air is descending to lower altitudes along the frontal surface.""@en .

,A katafront is a type of weather front characterized by warm air descending to lower altitudes along the frontal surface.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001710,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A weather front which exists in an equatorial trough separating the air of the Northern and Southern Hemispheres of an astronomical body.""@en

,The intertropical front is a type of weather front that intersects the atmosphere in tropical regions, acting as a boundary separating the air of the Northern and Southern Hemispheres of an astronomical body. This front is defined as a weather front existing in an equatorial trough. Additionally, the intertropical front is precisely synonymous with the term ""tropical front.""",4,True
:has_definition ""An air mass which is part of the free atmosphere, including the troposphere and stratosphere."" .

,Upper air is a type of air mass and is part of the free atmosphere, which at least includes some portion of the troposphere and stratosphere. It is defined as an air mass that is part of the free atmosphere, including the troposphere and stratosphere.",3,True

:has_definition ""An atmospheric layer which 1) is located above the planetary boundary layer, 2) in which the effect of friction between moving air masses and the planetary surface is negligible, and 3) in which the air is usually treated (dynamically) as an ideal fluid."" .

,The free atmosphere is a type of atmospheric layer and is also a type of entity that, at least in part, overlaps with something that is not within the atmospheric boundary layer. It is defined as an atmospheric layer which is located above the planetary boundary layer, where the effect of friction between moving air masses and the planetary surface is negligible, and in which the air is usually treated (dynamically) as an ideal fluid.",3,True
:has_definition ""A weather front which is part of a mass of upper air."" .

,An upper front is a type of weather front and is also a type of entity that is at least partially part of some upper air. It is defined as a weather front which is part of a mass of upper air.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001714,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A weather front which separates air behind a cold front from air ahead of a warm front."" .

,An occluded front is a type of weather front that is at least adjacent to both some cold front and some warm front. It has the definition of a weather front which separates air behind a cold front from air ahead of a warm front. Additionally, occluded front is broadly synonymous with occlusion.",5,True

:has_definition ""An occluded front which is adjacent to a cold front 1) that is moving away from the coldest air in the vicinity,  2) where the neighbouring cold front undercuts the neighbouring warm front in the occulsion zone, and 3) where the coldest air in the vicinity replaces less cold air towards the surface of the astronomical body."" .

,A cold occluded front is a specific type of occluded front characterized by its adjacency to a cold front that is moving away from the coldest air in the vicinity. This type of front is defined by three key features: 1) the neighboring cold front undercuts the neighboring warm front in the occlusion zone, 2) the coldest air in the vicinity replaces the less cold air towards the surface of the astronomical body, and 3) it is situated near a cold front that is moving away from the coldest air nearby.",2,True

:has_definition ""An occluded front which is adjacent to a warm front 1) that is moving in the direction of the coldest air in the vicinity, 2) where the original cold front is forced aloft at the warm front surface, and 3) where the coldest air is replaced by less cold air at the surface of the astronomical body."" .

,A warm occluded front is a specific type of occluded front, characterized by its adjacency to a warm front that is advancing towards the coldest air in the vicinity. This interaction results in the original cold front being lifted above the warm front surface, and subsequently, the coldest air at the surface of the astronomical body is replaced by air that is less cold.",2,True

:has_definition ""An occluded front which is 1) adjacent to a cold and a warm front with no appreciable difference between the temperatures of their bordering air masses and 2) which creates a pressure trough, a wind-shift line, a band of cloudiness, and precipitation at the surface of the astronomical body."" .

,A neutral occluded front is a specific type of occluded front characterized by its adjacency to both a cold and a warm front, where there is no significant difference in the temperatures of the bordering air masses. Furthermore, it is defined by the creation of a pressure trough, a wind-shift line, a band of cloudiness, and precipitation at the surface of the astronomical body.",2,True
:has_definition ""A cold front which forms behind a frontal cyclone and within a cold air mass with an appreciable horizontal temperature gradient."" .

,A secondary cold front, which is a type of cold front, is defined as a cold front that forms behind a frontal cyclone and within a cold air mass with an appreciable horizontal temperature gradient.",2,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric wind during which cold atmospheric gas flows downwards towards the surface of an astronomical body."" .

,Katabatic wind is a type of atmospheric wind that is defined as a phenomenon during which cold atmospheric gas flows downwards towards the surface of an astronomical body.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001720,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A katabatic wind during which atmospheric gas flows down the slope of an elevation, typically during periods of light larger-scale winds."" .

,Downslope katabatic wind is a type of katabatic wind and also falls under the category of phenomena that involve at least some slope. It is defined as a katabatic wind during which atmospheric gas flows down the slope of an elevation, typically during periods of light larger-scale winds.",3,True
:has_definition ""A katabatic wind which is driven by the cooling and subsequent sinking of atmospheric gas masses."" .

,A cooling-driven katabatic wind is a specific type of katabatic wind that is characterized by the cooling and subsequent sinking of atmospheric gas masses, which is its definition. This type of wind is the same as an entity that is both a katabatic wind and is at least causally downstream of or within an entity that involves the cooling of a gas occurring in some atmosphere. Thus, a cooling-driven katabatic wind is essentially associated with the phenomena that occur due to the cooling of atmospheric gases, situating it within the broader category of processes that are influenced by atmospheric cooling.",4,True

:has_definition ""A downslope katabatic wind during which warm, dry atmospheric gas descends along the lee side of a mountain range as a result of synoptic-scale, cross-barrier flow over that range.""

,Foehn wind is a type of downslope katabatic wind that has a specific interaction with at least one mountain range, playing a significant role in its formation. It is defined as a warm, dry atmospheric gas descends along the lee side of a mountain range as a result of synoptic-scale, cross-barrier flow over that range. Additionally, foehn wind is recognized by several narrow synonyms including Canterbury northwester, aspre, austru, chinook, favogn, halny wiatr, ljuka, sky sweeper, and zonda, highlighting its relevance and manifestation in various regional contexts.",12,True
:has_definition ""An environmental process during which a system does not thermally interact with its surroundings by virtue of a temperature difference between them."" .

,An adiabatic process is a type of environmental system process defined as an environmental process during which a system does not thermally interact with its surroundings by virtue of a temperature difference between them.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001724,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An adiabatic process during which no condensation of water vapor occurs and no liquid water is present."" .
,A dry adiabatic process is a type of adiabatic process defined as an adiabatic process during which no condensation of water vapor occurs, and no liquid water is present.",2,True
:has_definition ""An adiabatic process which involves air saturated with water vapour and the presence of liquid water.""

,The moist adiabatic process is a type of adiabatic process that also falls under the category of hydrological processes. It is characterized by involving not only air saturated with water vapor but also the presence of liquid water, essentially making it a process that includes at least a part of hydrological condensation. Furthermore, this process is specifically associated with the participation of water vapor-saturated air. It is defined as an adiabatic process which involves air saturated with water vapor and the presence of liquid water. Additionally, the moist adiabatic process is exactly synonymous with the saturation-adiabatic process.",6,True
:has_definition ""A katabatic wind during which the low temperature and increased density of a cold mass of atmospheric gas accelerates its descent.""

,Fall wind is identified as a type of katabatic wind, characterized by the phenomenon where the low temperature and increased density of a cold mass of atmospheric gas accelerates its descent. It closely aligns with the terms papagayo and vardar as its narrow synonyms, while it is also synonymously related to the term mistral.",5,True

:has_definition ""A fall wind which has a source so cold that, when the atmospheric gas reaches the lowlands or coast, the dynamic warming is insufficient to raise its temperature to the normal level for the region
column2: hence it appears as a cold wind."" .

column1: ,Bora is a type of fall wind characterized by its extremely cold source. When this atmospheric gas descends to the lowlands or coast, the dynamic warming it undergoes is not enough to elevate its temperature to the region's normal level, making it appear as a cold wind.",2,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric wind which rapidly forms, lasts for a duration in the order of minutes, and then rapidly decreases in speed."" .
,Squall wind is a type of atmospheric wind defined as an atmospheric wind which rapidly forms, lasts for a duration in the order of minutes, and then rapidly decreases in speed.",2,True
:has_definition ""A storm which is nautical, localised, and of high severity local storm considered as a whole: that is, winds and cloud mass and (if any) precipitation, thunder and lightning."" .

,A nautical squall is identified as a type of atmospheric storm that typically occurs within marine biomes. It is characterized as a kind of storm that encompasses elements or a combination of rainstorms, icestorms, electrostatic discharge processes, and convective storms. Furthermore, a nautical squall is defined as a localized, high severity nautical storm, which includes various components such as winds, cloud mass, and may also feature precipitation, thunder, and lightning, when considered in its entirety.",4,True

:has_definition ""A wind which is driven by the acceleration of flow through a gap, constriction, or channel resulting from large-scale pressure gradient, or by Venturi acceleration through a constricting passage."" .

,Jet effect wind is a type of atmospheric wind defined as a wind which is driven by the acceleration of flow through a gap, constriction, or channel resulting from large-scale pressure gradient, or by Venturi acceleration through a constricting passage.",2,True
:has_definition ""A jet-effect which passes through a gap, constriction, or channel between mountains in a mountain range or between ranges themselves.""

,Mountain gap wind is a type of jet effect wind defined as a jet-effect which passes through a gap, constriction, or channel between mountains in a mountain range or between ranges themselves. Furthermore, it has narrow synonyms including düsenwind, kossava, and tehuantepecer.",5,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric wind which moves up or down a slope and is driven by heating or cooling of that slope."" .

,Slope flow is a type of atmospheric wind and is also a type of phenomenon that involves at least one slope as a participant. It is defined as an atmospheric wind which moves up or down a slope and is driven by the heating or cooling of that slope.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001733,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An upslope wind driven by heating at the slope surface under fair-weather conditions."" .
,Anabatic wind, a type of slope flow, is defined as an upslope wind driven by heating at the slope surface under fair-weather conditions.",2,True
:has_definition ""A process during which direct stellar radiation interacts with a planetary surface."" .

,The insolation process is a type of radiation that involves a process during which direct stellar radiation interacts with a planetary surface. It is broadly synonymous with both incoming solar radiation and insolation.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001735,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material cooling process during which a portion of gaseous environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings."" .

,Cooling of a gas is defined as a material cooling process during which a portion of gaseous environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings. It is equivalent to the intersection of cooling of a fluid and processes that involve at least some gaseous environmental material as a participant. Moreover, cooling of a gas is a type of cooling of a fluid and also a type of process that involves at least some gaseous environmental material as a participant.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material cooling process during which a portion of liquid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings."" .

,The cooling of a liquid is defined as a material cooling process during which a portion of liquid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings. This process is identified as both a type of cooling of a fluid and a type of process that involves at least some liquid environmental material as a participant. Moreover, the cooling of a liquid is equivalent to the intersection of the cooling of a fluid and a process that involves at least some liquid environmental material as a participant.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material cooling process during which a portion of solid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings."" .

,The cooling of a solid is characterized as a material cooling process wherein a portion of solid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings. This process is synonymous with an occurrence that intersects both the material cooling process and an event that necessarily involves some solid environmental material. Therefore, the cooling of a solid falls under the category of material cooling processes and also qualifies as a type of event that involves at least one solid environmental material as a participant.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material cooling process during which a portion of fluid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings."" .

,Cooling of a fluid is defined as a material cooling process during which a portion of fluid environmental material loses thermal energy to its surroundings. It is a type of material cooling process and also falls under the category of processes that at least have a participant which is some fluid environmental material. This indicates that the cooling of a fluid is identical to the intersection of material cooling processes and processes that involve fluid environmental materials as participants.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001739,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material warming process during which the thermal energy in a volume of fluid increases."" .

,The warming of a fluid is identified as an instance of both a material warming process and a process that necessarily involves at least one participant from either gaseous environmental materials or liquid environmental materials. This definition encapsulates the essence of the warming of a fluid, placing it at the intersection of these two categories. In essence, the warming of a fluid is characterized as a material warming process during which the thermal energy within a fluid volume increases. This comprehensive understanding signifies that the warming of a fluid is not only a subtype of material warming processes but also a subtype of processes engaging with environmental materials in their gaseous or liquid states.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process of warming a fluid during which the thermal energy in a volume of gas increases."" .

,Warming of a gas is defined as a process during which the thermal energy in a volume of gas increases, and it is a type of warming of a fluid. Additionally, warming of a gas is also categorized as a type of process that involves at least some gaseous environmental material as a participant. Furthermore, the warming of a gas is equivalent to an intersection of the processes that involve warming of a fluid and those that include at least some gaseous environmental material as a participant.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process of warming a fluid which includes a volume of liquid as a participant."" .

,The warming of a liquid is defined as a process of warming a fluid which includes a volume of liquid as a participant. This process is identified as being the same as something that represents the intersection of the warming of a fluid and something that at least involves some liquid environmental material as a participant. Furthermore, the warming of a liquid is categorized as a type of warming of a fluid and also as a type of process that necessarily involves some liquid environmental material.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material warming process during which the thermal energy in a mass of solid material increases."" .

,The warming of a solid is defined as a material warming process during which the thermal energy in a mass of solid material increases. This process is identified as a specific type of material warming process and is also recognized as a process that involves at least some solid environmental material. Moreover, the warming of a solid is equivalent to the intersection of a material warming process and a process that involves at least some solid environmental material.",4,True
:has_definition ""A fluid astronomical body part which is plume shaped.""@en .

,Plume is a type of fluid astronomical body part and is also a type of something that at least has the quality of being plume-shaped. It is defined as a fluid astronomical body part which is plume-shaped.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001744,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A downslope katabatic wind which is generated by the cooling of atmospheric gas in contact with terrain surfaces.""

,Drainage wind, also known exactly as gravity wind, is a type of downslope katabatic wind that is driven by cooling. It is defined as a downslope katabatic wind which is generated by the cooling of atmospheric gas in contact with terrain surfaces.",4,True
:has_definition ""A front which shows very little mobility.""
,A quasi-stationary front is a type of weather front characterized by showing very little mobility, and it is also exactly known as a stationary front.",3,True
:has_definition ""A drainage wind which flows along the icy surface of a glacier."" .

,Glacier wind is a type of drainage wind, which is defined as a drainage wind that flows along the icy surface of a glacier. It is also a type of wind that involves at least one participant, which is an intersection of gaseous environmental material and an entity that is at least adjacent to some glacier.",3,True
:has_definition ""An advective transport process during which a fluid moves.""@en .

,Mass fluid flow is a type of advective transport process and is defined as an advective transport process during which a fluid moves. It is also a process that involves at least some fluid environmental material as a participant.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001748,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A mass fluid flow which moves  in the same direction as a planet's rotation, rotating due to a Coriolis effect.""

,Cyclonic circulation is a type of mass fluid flow that moves in the same direction as a planet's rotation, rotating due to a Coriolis effect. This is the definition of cyclonic circulation. Additionally, it has the exact synonym ""cyclonic rotation.""",3,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric storm during which winds flow with increased rates."" .

,A wind storm is a type of atmospheric storm which is defined as an atmospheric storm during which winds flow with increased rates.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001750,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A wind storm during which strong gusts of wind occur, transporting atmospheric gas in a linear fashion.""

,Straight line wind is a type of atmospheric wind characterized by a wind storm during which strong gusts of wind occur, transporting atmospheric gas in a linear fashion. It is also known exactly as ""hurricane of the prairie,"" ""plough winds,"" and ""thundergust.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A downdraft which is of high intensity and which spreads radially, with high speed, across the planetary surface upon reaching it.""@en .

,A downburst is a type of downdraft and is also a type of phenomenon that involves at least some planetary surface. It is defined as a high-intensity downdraft that spreads radially, with high speed, across the planetary surface upon reaching it.",3,True
:has_definition ""A macroburst during which no or very little rain is generated."" .

,A dry macroburst is a specific type of macroburst characterized by the absence or minimal generation of rain. It falls under the broader category of macrobursts and is defined as a macroburst during which no or very little rain is produced. This phenomenon is at least causally upstream of or intersects with events that involve water-based rainfall and are associated with a decreased rate of occurrence.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001753,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A macroburst during which large amounts of rain are generated."" .

,A wet macroburst is a type of macroburst that is causally upstream of or intersects with phenomena that involve water-based rainfall and exhibit an increased rate. It is defined as a macroburst during which large amounts of rain are generated.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001754,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A downburst during which high winds occur over an area less than four kilometres in diameter."" .

,A microburst is a type of downburst and it is defined as a downburst during which high winds occur over an area less than four kilometers in diameter.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001755,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A downburst during which high winds occur over an area larger than four kilometres in diameter."" .
,A macroburst is a type of downburst, which is defined as a downburst during which high winds occur over an area larger than four kilometres in diameter.",2,True
:has_definition ""A microburst during which large amounts of rain are generated."" .

,A wet microburst is a type of microburst that is causally upstream of or intersects with a phenomenon involving water-based rainfall and an increased rate of some quality. Furthermore, a wet microburst is defined as a microburst during which large amounts of rain are generated.",3,True
:has_definition ""A microburst during which no or very little rain is generated."" .

,A dry microburst is a type of microburst, which is defined as a microburst during which no or very little rain is generated. It falls within or is causally related to phenomena that involve an intersection of water-based rainfall and scenarios characterized by a decreased rate.",3,True
:has_definition ""A katabatic wind which is sudden and strong.""@en .
,Downdraft, a type of katabatic wind, is defined as a sudden and strong katabatic wind.",2,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which parts of an elastic material oscillate around their positions of equilibrium.""

,The vibration process is a type of material transport process, defined as a material transport process during which parts of an elastic material oscillate around their positions of equilibrium. Additionally, the vibration process has an exact synonym: vibration.",3,True
:has_definition ""A vibration process which occurs in the solid parts of an astronomical body as low-frequency acoustic waves pass through them.""

,The seismic vibration process is a type of vibration process that specifically occurs in some solid astronomical body part. It is defined as a vibration process that occurs in the solid parts of an astronomical body as low-frequency acoustic waves pass through them. Additionally, the seismic vibration process is also known by its related synonym, seismic activity.",4,True
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by a volcanic eruption.""

,Volcanic seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process which is caused by a volcanic eruption, and it is synonymous with volcanic seismicity. This type of seismic vibration process is also characterized as being at least causally downstream of or within a volcanic eruption. Moreover, volcanic seismic vibration is equivalent to the intersection of a seismic vibration process and an event that is at least causally downstream of or within a volcanic eruption.",5,True
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by the impact of a solid object on the surface of an astronomical body."" .

,Impact-driven seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process caused by the impact of a solid object on the surface of an astronomical body. It is simultaneously a type of seismic vibration process and also a type of event that is at least causally downstream of or within some impact event. Furthermore, impact-driven seismic vibration is identified as a type of process that has a causal agent, specifically something that is at the intersection of a meteor and an entity that possesses the quality of being solid. This highlights that impact-driven seismic vibration is synonymous with the intersection of seismic vibration processes and events causally related to or within an impact event.",5,True
:has_definition ""An impact event is a collision between material entities, resulting in changes in one or both of those entities."" .

,An impact event is a type of energy transfer process that encompasses various processes, including at least some parts of material transport and material transformation processes. It involves the participation of material entities. Furthermore, an impact event is defined as a collision between material entities, resulting in changes in one or both of those entities.",5,True
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by an explosion."" .

,Explosion-driven seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process caused by an explosion. It is identical to the intersection of something that involves a seismic vibration process and something that is at least causally downstream of or within some explosion process. Furthermore, explosion-driven seismic vibration is classified as a type of seismic vibration process and also as a type of something that is at least causally downstream of or within some explosion process.",4,True
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by mass wasting."" .

,Mass wasting driven seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process that is caused by mass wasting. It is a type of seismic vibration process and also falls within the category of being at least causally downstream of or within some aspect of mass wasting. This means that mass wasting driven seismic vibration is equivalent to something that intersects the processes of seismic vibration and is either caused by or is a part of mass wasting.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001766,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by the collapose of a material entity, sending kinetic energy into astronomical body."" .

,Collapse-driven seismic vibration is the same as something that intersects a seismic vibration process and something that is at least causally downstream of or within a structural collapse process. It is a type of seismic vibration process and also a type of something that is at least causally downstream of or within some structural collapse process. Collapse-driven seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process caused by the collapse of a material entity, which sends kinetic energy into an astronomical body.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which the ability of a material entity to maintain its internal organisation fails, resulting in deformation and a breakdown of that organisation."" .

,The structural collapse process is a type of energy transfer process, defined as a process during which the ability of a material entity to maintain its internal organization fails, resulting in deformation and a breakdown of that organization.",2,True
:has_definition ""A structural collapse process during which the walls of cave are unable to support the load placed upon them."" .

,Cave collapse is a type of structural collapse process and something that involves at least one cave as a participant. It is defined as a structural collapse process during which the walls of a cave are unable to support the load placed upon them.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001769,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A seismic vibration process which is caused by an earthquake."" .

,Earthquake-driven seismic vibration is defined as a seismic vibration process caused by an earthquake. This process is identical to the intersection of a seismic vibration process and something that is at least causally downstream of or within an earthquake. Furthermore, earthquake-driven seismic vibration is categorized as a type of seismic vibration process as well as a type of phenomenon that is at least causally downstream of or within an earthquake.",4,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which precedes the strongest tectonic earthquake in a series, linked to the same release of energy in the crust."" .

,A foreshock is a type of tectonic earthquake that precedes the strongest tectonic earthquake in a series, linked to the same release of energy in the crust. It is defined as a tectonic earthquake which at least precedes some mainshock.",3,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which 1) is embedded in a series of tectonic earthquakes, linked to the same release of energy in the crust and 2) has the largest magnitude of the series."" .

,Mainshock is a type of tectonic earthquake, defined as a tectonic earthquake that is embedded in a series of tectonic earthquakes, linked to the same release of energy in the crust, and has the largest magnitude of the series.",2,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which 1) is embedded in a series of tectonic earthquakes, linked to the same release of energy in the crust and 2) occurs after the mainshock."" .
,An aftershock is a type of tectonic earthquake and is defined as a tectonic earthquake that is part of a series of tectonic earthquakes linked to the same release of energy in the crust
column2: it occurs after the mainshock. Furthermore, an aftershock is a type of event that is always preceded by some mainshock.",3,True

column1: :has_definition ""A fault across which older rocks are pushed above (away from the core of an astronomical body) younger rocks."" .
,A thrust fault is a type of geological fault, defined as a fault across which older rocks are pushed above (away from the core of an astronomical body) younger rocks.",2,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which occurs along a thrust fault which does not breach the surface of an astronomical body."" .

,A blind thrust earthquake is a type of tectonic earthquake and is also defined as a tectonic earthquake that occurs along a thrust fault which does not breach the surface of an astronomical body. This type of earthquake is associated with at least having a participant, specifically a blind thrust fault.",3,True
:has_definition ""A thrust fault which does not breach the surface of an astronomical body."" .

,A blind thrust fault is a type of thrust fault and falls under the category of features that are contained within some subsurface zone of an astronomical body. It is defined as a thrust fault that does not breach the surface of an astronomical body.,3,True

:has_definition ""An environmental zone which includes those regions of an astronomical body which are not exposed to its atmosphere or space."" .

,The subsurface zone of an astronomical body is a type of environmental zone, and it is also considered a part of or adjacent to areas that are not within the atmosphere or outer space of an astronomical body. This zone encompasses regions of an astronomical body that are not exposed to its atmosphere or outer space, defining it as an environmental zone that includes those regions which are beneath the exposed surface.",4,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which has two or more mainshocks of similar magnitude, and which originate from the same fracture zone and stress field."" .

,A multiplet tectonic earthquake is a type of tectonic earthquake that is characterized by having at least two mainshock components, which are part of the same fracture zone and stress field. This implies that a multiplet tectonic earthquake consists of two or more mainshocks of similar magnitude. It is defined as a tectonic earthquake with this specific characteristic and is also broadly synonymous with the term ""multiplet earthquake.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which occurs at the boundary between two tectonic plates."" .

,An interplate earthquake is a type of tectonic earthquake and is also a type of event that involves at least one tectonic plate as a participant. It is defined as a tectonic earthquake that occurs at the boundary between two tectonic plates.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001779,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A tectonic earthquake which occurs within the interior parts of a tectonic plate."" .

,An intraplate earthquake is a type of tectonic earthquake and it is also a type of event that involves at least one tectonic plate as a participant. It is defined as a tectonic earthquake that occurs within the interior parts of a tectonic plate.,3,True

,The desert ecosystem is a type of ecosystem that is synonymous with an intersection of an ecosystem and something that is primarily determined by a desert. :has_definition ""A solid astronomical body part which is part of the landmass of that body."" .

,A part of a landmass is defined as a solid astronomical body part which is part of the landmass of that body. It is also identified as a type of solid astronomical body part and a type of something that is at least part of some planetary landmass. Furthermore, it is equivalent to something that intersects with a solid astronomical body part and something that is at least part of some planetary landmass.",4,True
:has_definition ""A large continuous area of land, either surrounded by sea or contiguous with another landmass."" .
,A landmass is a type of land that is defined as a large continuous area of land, either surrounded by sea or contiguous with another landmass.",2,True
:has_definition ""A surface of an astronomical body which is part of a water body present on that body."" .

,A liquid surface of an astronomical body, which is defined as a surface of an astronomical body that is part of a water body present on that body, is a type of surface of an astronomical body.",2,True
:has_definition ""A part of an astronomical body which is composed of a continuous medium bearing liquid, gaseous, and solid material in variable quantities.""@en .

,A compound astronomical body part is equivalent to an intersection of an astronomical body part and something that is at least primarily composed of materials which are a combination of gaseous, solid, and liquid environmental materials. Furthermore, a compound astronomical body part is categorized as a type of astronomical body part and also as a type that is primarily composed of a mix of gaseous, solid, and liquid environmental materials. :has_definition ""A surface layer of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of solid material and is not covered by oceans or other bodies of water."" .

,An inland sea, which is also precisely referred to as an epeiric sea or an epicontinental sea, is defined as a sea that shallowly covers central areas of continents during periods of high sea level, resulting in marine transgressions. This type of sea is a specific categorization within seas.",4,True

,An aquatic ecosystem is a type of ecosystem that is the same as something that intersects an ecosystem and something at least determined by a water body. Moreover, it is a type of something that is at least determined by some water body.",3,True
