,A safe environment is categorized within environmental systems and is defined by its quality. Specifically, it is an environment in which material entities face a low likelihood of damage or destruction.",2,True
:has_definition ""An andosol which derives its silica content from glass and tephra ejected during a volcanic eruption."" .

,Volcanic soil is a type of andosol, which is characterized as a type of material that at least partly comprises elements found in both environmental material and substances that primarily derive from tephra. Furthermore, volcanic soil is defined as an andosol that obtains its silica content from glass and tephra expelled during a volcanic eruption.",3,True
:has_definition ""An environmental process during which momentum is transferred from one material entity to another."" .

,The momentum transfer process is a type of energy transfer process and also falls under the category of processes that involve entities with at least the quality of momentum and include the participation of some material entity. Furthermore, it is defined as an environmental process during which momentum is transferred from one material entity to another.",3,True
:has_definition ""A momentum transfer process which unfolds as winds generate drag at the bottom of the atmosphere,coupled to dynamical forcing at the surface of the ocean."" .

,The atmosphere-ocean momentum transfer process is categorized under the broader category of momentum transfer processes. This specific type of process is characterized by involving at least a part of the atmospheric wind and includes the ocean and the atmosphere as participants. It is defined as a momentum transfer process that occurs when winds generate drag at the bottom of the atmosphere, which is coupled to dynamical forcing at the surface of the ocean.",5,True
:has_definition ""A rate which inheres in an atmosphere-ocean momentum transfer process."" .

,Ocean surface stress is a type of environmental system process quality and a type of rate. It is also characterized by being part of some atmosphere-ocean momentum transfer process. Furthermore, it is defined as a rate which inheres in an atmosphere-ocean momentum transfer process.",4,True
:has_definition ""Frost which is composed of interlocking ice crystals formed by vapour transfer (sublimation followed by deposition) of water vapour on some surface.""

,Hoar is a type of frost that is defined as frost composed of interlocking ice crystals formed by the vapour transfer (sublimation followed by deposition) of water vapour on some surface. It has exact synonyms including hoar frost and white frost.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001846,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Hoar which is usually cup-shaped and facetted and which forms within dry, low-density snow beneath the snow surface."" .

,Depth hoar is a type of hoar and it falls under the category of something that is at least adjacent to something, which intersects with something that intersects with something that includes the surface layer. Additionally, it is a part of something that is at least composed primarily of snow and something that is at least adjacent to the atmosphere. Depth hoar is defined as hoar that is usually cup-shaped and faceted, forming within dry, low-density snow beneath the snow surface.",3,True

,hoarfrost is a type of hoar.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001848,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""Water ice which 1) has a white or milky and opaque appearance, 2) has a granular texture, and 3) is formed as a result of the deposition and rapid freezing of supercooled water drops as they make contact with an exposed object.""@en .

,Rime is a type of frost and also a type of something that possesses at least some quality of being an intersection of opaque and granular. It is defined as water ice that 1) has a white or milky and opaque appearance, 2) features a granular texture, and 3) forms as a result of the deposition and rapid freezing of supercooled water drops upon making contact with an exposed object.",3,True

,glaze is a type of hoar.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001850,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental material which is primarily composed of minute ice crystals forming a fuzzy layer over a cold surface by direct deposition of water vapor."" .

,Frost is an environmental material that is primarily composed of water ice crystals. It forms as a result of the desublimation of water vapor into ice, creating a fuzzy layer over a cold surface that is at least adjacent to some surface layer. Essentially, frost is defined as an environmental material which is primarily composed of minute ice crystals forming a fuzzy layer over a cold surface by direct deposition of water vapor.",5,True

:curator_note ""This will usually be a part of a rocky planet's crust, with that planet being of sufficient size and age to allow geothermal activity. Such activity may also arise from gravitational effects of large bodies near a rocky astronomical body.""
:has_definition ""A field in which geothermal processes occur."" .

,A geothermally active field is a type of field that is defined as a field in which geothermal processes occur. This type of field is also a type of entity that has, at a minimum, a part capable of processes that intersect with those that at least realize some geothermal energy. The curator's note on geothermally active fields usually indicates that they are part of a rocky planet's crust. For geothermal activity to occur, the planet must be of sufficient size and age. Additionally, such activity may arise from the gravitational effects of large bodies near a rocky astronomical body.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which one entity loses energy to another entity."" .

,The energy transfer process is a type of environmental system process and is defined as a process during which one entity loses energy to another entity.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001853,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being located in the vicinity of - but not adjacent to or within - a glacier or ice sheet."" .

,Periglacial is a type of position characterized by a unique intersection with material entities located in regions that are part of either an ice sheet or a glacier. Furthermore, periglacial is defined by a positional quality that is inherent in a bearer due to the bearer's location being in the vicinity of, but not adjacent to or within, a glacier or ice sheet.",3,True
:has_definition ""A geothermally active field within which geothermally heated aqueous fluids are discharged from the the surface of a rocky planet."" .

,A hydrothermal field is a type of geothermally active field that encompasses elements such as hydrothermal vents, hydrothermal seeps, and hydrothermally influenced sediments. It is defined as a geothermally active field within which geothermally heated aqueous fluids are discharged from the surface of a rocky planet.",3,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which the volume of liquid entity increases."" .

,The liquid accumulation process is characterized by being equivalent to an intersection involving the material accumulation process and a process that involves, at minimum, some liquid environmental material as a participant. Additionally, the liquid accumulation process is identified as a type of material accumulation process and also as a type that necessitates the involvement of some liquid environmental material. It is defined as a material accumulation process during which the volume of a liquid entity increases.",4,True

:has_definition ""An infrared radiation process which 1) transmits radiant energy has wavelengths between 3.0 and 100 μm, 2) is emitted from a planet and its atmosphere out to space in the form of thermal radiation.""

,Outgoing longwave radiation is a type of infrared radiation defined as an infrared radiation process that transmits radiant energy with wavelengths between 3.0 and 100 μm and is emitted from a planet and its atmosphere out into space in the form of thermal radiation. It is exactly synonymous with both outgoing long-wave radiation and up-welling long-wave radiation, and has a narrow synonym as terrestrial long-wave flux.",5,True
:has_definition ""An area density which inheres in a clouds by virtue of some influence exerted their mass exerts on a given area."" .

,Cloud cover is a type of area density and also a type of something that is at least characteristic of some cloud. It is defined as an area density which inheres in clouds by virtue of some influence exerted by their mass on a given area.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001859,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A temperature of air at which air become saturated with water vapour and below which airborne water vapour will condense to form liquid water (dew)."" .

,Dew point is a type of temperature of air, defined as the temperature at which air becomes saturated with water vapor and below which airborne water vapor will condense to form liquid water, known as dew.",2,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric wind which 1) has an increased rate relative to other winds in the same region and 2) is followed by a lull."" .

,Wind gust is a type of atmospheric wind and has a definition as an atmospheric wind which 1) has an increased rate relative to other winds in the same region and 2) is followed by a lull. Moreover, wind gust has a broad synonym, gust.",3,True
:has_definition ""An electromagnetic radiation process during which radiant energy with wavelengths in the visible, near-ultraviolet, or near-infrared spectra is realised.""

,Shortwave radiation is a type of electromagnetic radiation and is defined as an electromagnetic radiation process during which radiant energy with wavelengths in the visible, near-ultraviolet, or near-infrared spectra is released. Furthermore, shortwave radiation is exactly synonymous with short-wave radiation.",3,True

:has_definition ""Electromagnetic radidation which involves radiant energy in a spectral range (wave band) between 400 to 700 nanometers, that photosynthetic organisms are able to use in the process of photosynthesis.""

,Photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) is a type of electromagnetic radiation defined as electromagnetic radiation that involves radiant energy in a spectral range (waveband) between 400 to 700 nanometers, which photosynthetic organisms can use in the process of photosynthesis.",3,True
:has_definition ""The concentration of carbon dioxide when measured in air that is part of an atmosphere."" .

,The concentration of carbon dioxide in an atmosphere is defined as the concentration of carbon dioxide when measured in air that is part of an atmosphere. It is equivalent to something that intersects the concentration of and something characterized by being an intersection of carbon dioxide and at least part of some atmosphere. Furthermore, this concentration is a type of concentration and also a type of something characterized by being an intersection of carbon dioxide and at least part of some atmosphere.",4,True
:has_definition ""A planned process during which an oil or gas well is modified."" .

,Well intervention is a planned process that is a type of operation involving at least one participant, which can be either an oil well or a gas well. Furthermore, this process requires homo sapiens as the causal agent. It is defined as a planned process during which an oil or gas well is modified.",4,True
:has_definition ""A well intervention during which the production of an oil or gas well is increased by improving the flow of hydrocarbons from the reservoir into the well bore."" .

,Well stimulation, a type of well intervention, is defined as a process during which the production of an oil or gas well is increased by improving the flow of hydrocarbons from the reservoir into the well bore.",2,True
:has_definition ""A well stimulation technique during which bedrock formations are fractured through the injection of pressurized proppant-bearing liquid into a well-bore.""

,Hydraulic fracturing is a type of well stimulation, an anthropogenic environmental process, and involves a process that includes at least some fracking liquid as a participant. It is defined as a well stimulation technique during which bedrock formations are fractured through the injection of pressurized proppant-bearing liquid into a wellbore. Moreover, hydraulic fracturing has several exact synonyms, including frac'ing, fraccing, fracing, fracking, hydrofracking, and hydrofracturing.",10,True
:has_definition ""A liquid environmental material which is composed primarily of water ammended with thickening agents and proppants.""

,Fracking liquid is a manufactured product that falls under the category of anthropogenic and liquid environmental materials. It is notably composed primarily of liquid water. Fracking liquid is defined as a liquid environmental material, primarily composed of water but amended with thickening agents and proppants. Furthermore, it is narrowly synonymous with fracking water.",6,True
:has_definition ""A well which has been drilled in order to extract natrual gas from subterranean reservoirs and bring it to the surface."" .

,A gas well is a type of well with the definition being a well that has been drilled to extract natural gas from subterranean reservoirs and bring it to the surface.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001871,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A depression in the ground resembling a hole or cavity, either natural or anthropogenic."" .
,A pit is a type of depressed landform and is defined as a depression in the ground resembling a hole or cavity, either natural or anthropogenic.",2,True
:has_definition ""A pit which is used for the collection and storage of manure."" .
,A manure pit, which is a type of pit and also a type of entity that constitutes at least part of some manure storage space, is defined as a pit used for the collection and storage of manure.",3,True
:has_definition ""A construction in which eggs are hatched under artificial conditions."" .

,A hatchery is a type of human construction and also a type of structure that at least has some part of an agricultural ecosystem as its component. It is defined as a construction in which eggs are hatched under artificial conditions.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001874,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hatchery in which the eggs of poultry are hatched under artificial conditions.""^^xsd:string .

,A poultry hatchery is a type of hatchery defined as a facility where the eggs of poultry are hatched under artificial conditions.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001875,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A debris flow which is causally preceded by rainfall.""@en .

,Debris flow following rainfall is equivalent to an intersection of debris flow and something that is at least causally downstream of or within some water-based rainfall. It is classified as a type of debris flow and also as a type of phenomenon that is at least causally downstream of or within some water-based rainfall. Furthermore, debris flow following rainfall is defined as a debris flow which is causally preceded by rainfall.",4,True
:has_definition ""Snow which is composed of heavily rimed particles typically 2 to 5 millimeters in diameter (0.1 to 0.2 inch).""@en

,Graupel is a type of snow that is also known as snow pellets. It is primarily composed of rime and is defined as snow composed of heavily rimed particles, typically 2 to 5 millimeters in diameter (0.1 to 0.2 inch).",4,True

,A transient tracer is a type of tracer that is characterized by being a combination of several elements, including chlorofluorocarbons, argon 39 atoms, tritium atoms, helium 3 atoms, sulfur hexafluoride, and carbon 14 atoms.",2,True
:has_definition ""A transient tracer role which inheres in chemical entities in seawater.""@en .

,An oceanic transient tracer, which also has the broad synonym ""marine transient tracer,"" is a type of transient tracer. It is defined as having a role that inheres in chemical entities in seawater.",3,True
:has_definition ""A positional quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer in being in physical contact with, or close to, a glacial margin."" .

,Proglacial is categorized as a type of position and is described as a characteristic that intersects with a material entity that is at least adjacent to a glacier. Furthermore, proglacial is defined as a positional quality that is inherent in a bearer due to the bearer being in physical contact with, or close to, a glacial margin.",3,True
:has_definition ""A positional quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer in being in physical contact with or below a glacial bed."" .

,Subglacial is categorized as a type of position and is specifically associated with entities that have the characteristic of being at the intersection of a material entity and entities that are at least adjacent to a glacial bed. Furthermore, subglacial is defined as a positional quality which is inherent in a bearer due to the bearer being in physical contact with or situated below a glacial bed.",3,True
:has_definition ""A positional quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer in being in physical contact with the upper surface of a glacier or objects on top of the glacier."" .

,Supraglacial is a type of position and also a type of something characterized by at least intersecting with material entities and entities that are not subglacial, as well as being adjacent to some glacial surface layer. Moreover, supraglacial is defined as a positional quality that exists in a bearer due to the bearer being in physical contact with the upper surface of a glacier or objects on top of the glacier.",3,True
:has_definition ""Hoar which a) forms on surfaces, b) occurs when the temperature of the surface is colder than the air above and colder than the frost point of that air."" .

,Surface hoar is a type of hoar, and it is also a type of entity that is adjacent to something which intersects with something that itself intersects with the surface layer. This entity is also composed primarily of snow and is adjacent to the atmosphere. The definition of surface hoar, known as Hoar, includes that it forms on surfaces and occurs when the temperature of the surface is colder than the air above and colder than the frost point of that air.",3,True
:has_definition ""A water ice crystal which is a part of a deposit of hoarfrost and which only grows by desublimation.""

,A hoar crystal is a type of water ice crystal and is also known as a white frost crystal or, more precisely, a hoar frost crystal. It is defined as a water ice crystal that is a part of a deposit of hoarfrost and grows exclusively by desublimation, which is the process where water vapor turns directly into ice. This means that a hoar crystal forms as a result of the desublimation of water vapor into ice.",5,True
:has_definition ""A landform which occurs on the surface of an astronomical body.""@en

,Surface landform is a type of landform that is defined as a landform which occurs on the surface of an astronomical body. Additionally, it is synonymously related to the term geographic feature.",3,True
:has_definition ""A landform which is submerged underneath a body of liquid.""@en .

,A submerged landform is a type of landform with the definition of being a landform which is submerged underneath a body of liquid.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001886,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A solid astronomical body part which has been formed from and is composed primarily of the matter of that astronomical body.""@en .

,A landform is a type of solid astronomical body part and is defined as a solid astronomical body part that has been formed from and is composed primarily of the matter of that astronomical body.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001887,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A paper product which has been manufactured to facilitate the writing of letters.""@en .

,Letter paper is a type of paper product that has been manufactured to facilitate the writing of letters.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001888,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of calcium hydroxide flows.""@en .
,A calcic spring, which is a type of mineral spring, is defined as a mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of calcium hydroxide flows.",2,True
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of lithium salts flows.""@en .

,Lithia spring is a type of mineral spring defined as a mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of lithium salts flows.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001890,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A spring through which water with elevated concentrations of iron salts flows.""@en .

,A chalybeate spring is a type of mineral spring defined as a spring through which water with elevated concentrations of iron salts flows.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001891,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A spring through which water with elevated concentrations of hydrated double sulfate aluminium salts flows.""@en .
,Alum spring is a type of mineral spring, defined as a spring through which water with elevated concentrations of hydrated double sulfate aluminium salts flows.",2,True
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of sodium, calcium, or magnesium salts flows.""@en

,A salt spring, which is a type of mineral spring, is defined as a mineral spring through which water with elevated concentrations of sodium, calcium, or magnesium salts flows. It is also exactly synonymous with a saline spring.",3,True
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with a high pH flows.""@en .

,An alkaline spring is a type of mineral spring defined as a mineral spring through which water with a high pH flows.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001895,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with elevated levels of dissolved carbon dioxide gas flows.""@en .

,A soda spring is a type of mineral spring characterized by water with elevated levels of dissolved carbon dioxide gas flowing through it.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001896,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A mineral spring through which water with elevated levels of radioactive material flows.""@en .

,A radioactive spring is classified as a type of mineral spring, distinguished by being a kind of entity that includes, at least in part, an intersection of water and entities that possess the quality of being radioactive. Furthermore, a radioactive spring is defined as a mineral spring through which water containing elevated levels of radioactive material flows.",3,True
:has_definition ""A spring through which water with a neutral pH flows.""@en .

,A neutral spring is a type of spring characterized by the fact that it is a spring through which water with a neutral pH flows.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001898,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A spring through which water with a low pH flows.""@en .
,An acidic spring, which is a type of spring, is defined as a spring through which water with a low pH flows. It is broadly synonymous with the term acid spring.",3,True

,reef is a type of hydrographic feature.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01003000,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A vehicle designed to fly in outer space.""@en .

,A spacecraft is a type of vehicle that is defined as a vehicle designed to fly in outer space.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01003001,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A disposition of a material entity which is realised when it is saturated with liquid water.""@en .

,Water holding capacity is a type of disposition, and it is also a characteristic that is at least found in some material entities. It is defined as the disposition of a material entity which is realized when it is saturated with liquid water.",3,True
:has_definition ""A mass of solid material which is either 1) a minute fragment of a larger mass or 2) one of a collection of small masses composing an aggregate.""

,A particle is a type of mass of solid material and is also a type of something that, at the very least, is part of some particulate environmental material. Moreover, a particle is a type of something that is at least surrounded by a union of gaseous and liquid environmental materials. It is defined as a mass of solid material which is either a minute fragment of a larger mass or one of a collection of small masses composing an aggregate. Additionally, particle has a related synonym, which is ""grain.""",5,True

:has_definition ""A particle which 1) is composed primarily of hydrous aluminium phyllosilicate minerals, in turn composed of aluminium and silicon ions bonded into tiny, thin plates by interconnecting oxygen and hydroxide ions, and 2) is or was part of a portion of clay.""@en

,A particle of clay is a type of particle and also a type of entity that is part of or derived from at least a portion of clay. It is defined as a particle which 1) is composed primarily of hydrous aluminium phyllosilicate minerals, these minerals themselves are composed of aluminium and silicon ions bonded into tiny, thin plates by interconnecting oxygen and hydroxide ions, and 2) is or was part of a portion of clay. Moreover, a particle of clay has an exact synonym: clay particle.",4,True
:has_definition ""A one-dimensional temporal region which spans the duration an astronomical body completes one rotation on its axis.""@en .
,A day is a type of one-dimensional temporal region, defined as a one-dimensional temporal region which spans the duration an astronomical body completes one rotation on its axis.",2,True
:has_definition ""A day during which water-based rainfall occurs.""@en .

,A rainy day is categorized as a type of day and is defined as a day during which water-based rainfall occurs. It is also described as a type of occurrence during which some water-based rainfall starts.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01003007,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Percolation during which water moves through the interstices of soil.""@en

,Percolation of water through soil is a type of water flow process, percolation, and something that at least has part some water infiltration into soil. It is defined as percolation during which water moves through the interstices of soil and has the exact synonym ""water percolation through soil.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which a fluid is filtered through porous soild or semi-solid materials.""@en .

,Percolation is a type of material transport process that involves the movement of fluid environmental materials. Specifically, it entails the movement of fluids that are both environmental materials and possess qualities of being porous. This process is defined as a material transport process during which a fluid is filtered through porous solid or semi-solid materials.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which a liquid which is not absorbed or otherwise held in place by a material is transported away from its location.""@en .

,The drainage process is a type of material transport process, which occurs in some environmental material and involves the movement of liquid environmental material. It is defined as a material transport process during which a liquid, which is not absorbed or otherwise held in place by a material, is transported away from its location.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process which arises spontaneously due to physical heterogeneities in a portion of a material and forces which act throughout its volume.""@en .

,The convective transport process is defined as a material transport process that arises spontaneously due to physical heterogeneities in a portion of a material and forces acting throughout its volume. It is identified as a type of material transport process and also as a type that has at least some convective characteristics. Furthermore, the convective transport process is equivalent to the intersection of material transport processes and processes that have at least some convective characteristics.",4,True

:has_definition ""A physical quality of a process which is characteristic of processes that transport material within a volume due to the combined effects of material property heterogeneity and body forces across that volume.""@en .

,Convective is a type of physical quality of a process, defined as a characteristic of processes that transport material within a volume due to the combined effects of material property heterogeneity and body forces across that volume.",2,True

:has_definition ""A physical quality of a process which is characteristic of process that transport material without, themselves, changing the qualities of those materials or the processes that are unfolding within them.""@en .

,Advective is a type of physical quality of a process, defined as a characteristic of processes that transport material without changing the qualities of those materials or the processes unfolding within them.",2,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which material moves from a region of higher concentration to a region of lower concentration.""@en .

,The material diffusion process, which is a type of material transport process, is defined as a material transport process during which material moves from a region of higher concentration to a region of lower concentration. This process is also broadly known as diffusion.",3,True
:has_definition ""An energy transfer process during which a material entity receives energy through radiation.""@en .

,Irradiation is a type of energy transfer process that involves a material entity receiving energy through radiation. This process has at least one participant, a surface layer, and is causally downstream of or within some form of radiation. It is defined as an energy transfer process during which a material entity receives energy through radiation.",4,True
:has_definition ""Irradiation during which a material entity receives energy through ionizing radiation.""@en

,Irradiation by ionizing radiation is a type of irradiation that involves a material entity receiving energy through ionizing radiation. This type of irradiation is characterized by the fact that it includes at least a part of ionizing radiation. Additionally, irradiation by ionizing radiation is exactly synonymous with irradiation by ionising radiation.",4,True
:has_definition ""Irradiation during which a material entity receives energy through non-ionizing radiation.""@en

,Irradiation by non-ionizing radiation is both a type of irradiation and something that encompasses parts or unions of various forms of radiation, including shortwave radiation, photosynthetically active radiation, microwave radiation, radio wave radiation, infrared radiation, and visible spectrum radiation. It is defined as the process during which a material entity receives energy through non-ionizing radiation. Additionally, irradiation by non-ionizing radiation is exactly synonymous with irradiation by non-ionising radiation.",4,True
:has_definition ""Irradiation during which a material entity receives energy through photosynthetically active radiation.""@en .

,Irradiation by photosynthetically active radiation is a type of irradiation by non-ionizing radiation and is also a type of something that at least has part some photosynthetically active radiation. It is defined as irradiation during which a material entity receives energy through photosynthetically active radiation.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01003018,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Wave energy which inheres in perpendicular electric and magnetic fields and which is realised when they oscillate and propagate.""@en

,Electromagnetic wave energy, which is a type of wave energy, is also a form of energy realized in some electromagnetic radiation. It is defined as the wave energy that inheres in perpendicular electric and magnetic fields, realized when these fields oscillate and propagate. Additionally, electromagnetic wave energy is synonymously known as electromagnetic radiant energy.",4,True
:has_definition ""Energy which inheres in a wave and is realised during its propagation.""@en .

,Wave energy is a type of energy that is inherent in a wave and is realized during its propagation.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000000,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A hypodermic needle is a medical instrument made from a hollow needle. It is commonly used with a syringe to inject substances into the body of an organism.""^^xsd:string .

,A hypodermic needle is a type of medical instrument defined as a medical instrument made from a hollow needle. It is commonly used with a syringe to inject substances into the body of an organism.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000001,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A textile is a manufactured product comprised of a network of natural or artificial fibers (often referred to as thread or yarn).""^^xsd:string .
,Textile is a type of manufactured product, defined as a product comprised of a network of natural or artificial fibers, often referred to as thread or yarn.",2,True
:has_definition ""Bedclothing is a textile covering used on a bed as a sheet, blanket, or pillowcase.""^^xsd:string .
,Bedclothing is a type of textile that is defined as a textile covering used on a bed, such as a sheet, blanket, or pillowcase.",2,True

:has_definition ""A pockmark field is an undersea feature formed by shallow seabed depressions, typically several tens of metres across and a few metres deep. Generally, they are formed in soft, fine-grained seabed sediments by the escape of fluids (gas or water, but mainly methane) into the water column.""^^xsd:string .

,A pockmark field is the same as an intersection of a field and something that is at least part of some sea floor, and something that at least has part of some marine pockmark. It is a type of field, and also a type of something that is at least part of some sea floor, as well as a type of something that at least has part of some marine pockmark. A pockmark field is defined as an undersea feature formed by shallow seabed depressions, typically several tens of meters across and a few meters deep. Generally, they are formed in soft, fine-grained seabed sediments by the escape of fluids (gas or water, but mainly methane) into the water column.",5,True

:has_definition ""Nesting material is an animal habitation consisting of matierals used to cushion, insulate and protect the young of the organism. The adult will use the material to form a protective structure to house and raise their young. Nests are built primarily by birds, but also by mammals, fish, insects and reptiles.""^^xsd:string .

,Nesting material is a type of environmental material, defined as an animal habitation consisting of materials used to cushion, insulate, and protect the young of the organism. The adult uses the material to form a protective structure to house and raise their young. Nests are built primarily by birds, but also by mammals, fish, insects, and reptiles.",2,True
:has_definition ""Tissue culture is the culture of cells, tissues or organs in a nutrient medium under sterile conditions.""^^xsd:string .
,Tissue culture is a type of planned process, defined as the culture of cells, tissues, or organs in a nutrient medium under sterile conditions.",2,True
:has_definition ""A cell culture is a growth of cells in vitro in an artificial medium for experimental research.""^^xsd:string .

,Cell culture is a type of organic material that is defined as a growth of cells in vitro in an artificial medium for experimental research.,2,True

:has_definition ""Plant tissue culture is the growth or maintenance of plant cells, tissues, organs or whole plants in vitro.""^^xsd:string .
,Plant tissue culture is a type of tissue culture that involves the growth or maintenance of plant cells, tissues, organs, or whole plants in vitro.",2,True

:has_definition ""Organ culture is the aseptic culture of complete living organs of animals and plants outside the body in a suitable culture medium. Animal organs must be small enough to allow the nutrients in the culture medium to penetrate all the cells.""^^xsd:string .

,Organ culture is a type of tissue culture, defined as the aseptic culture of complete living organs of animals and plants outside the body in a suitable culture medium. For animal organs, they must be small enough to allow the nutrients in the culture medium to penetrate all the cells.",2,True

:has_definition ""An organic material which is primarily composed of some natural bodily fluid or secretion such as blood, semen, saliva, blood plasma, intracellular and interstitial fluids.""^^xsd:string .

,Bodily fluid material is a type of organic material that is at least composed primarily of some cerumen. It is defined as an organic material which is primarily composed of some natural bodily fluid or secretion such as blood, semen, saliva, blood plasma, intracellular, and interstitial fluids.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of blood, a bodily fluid composed of blood plasma and blood cells suspended within the plasma that circulates around the organism's body. Blood performs may important functions including the supplying of oxygen and nutrients, removal of waste, circulation of white blood cells, detection of antibodes, coagulation, transportation of antibodies and the regulation of pH and body temperature.""^^xsd:string .

,Blood material is a type of caro 0000000, bodily fluid material, and something that is at least composed primarily of blood. It is defined as a bodily fluid material primarily composed of blood, which itself is a bodily fluid made of blood plasma and blood cells suspended within the plasma that circulates around the organism's body. Blood carries out many important functions, including supplying oxygen and nutrients, removing waste, circulating white blood cells, detecting antibodies, coagulating, transporting antibodies, and regulating pH and body temperature.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of amniotic fluid, a bodily fluid consisting of watery liquid surrounding and cushioning a growing fetus within the amnion. It allows the fetus to move freely without the walls of the uterus being too tight against its body. Buoyancy is also provided.""^^xsd:string .

,Amniotic fluid material is a type of bodily fluid material and is primarily composed of amniotic fluid. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which consists of a watery liquid surrounding and cushioning a growing fetus within the amnion. This fluid allows the fetus to move freely without the uterus walls being too tight against its body and also provides buoyancy.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000022,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of excreta, bodily fluids consisting of matter which contains the waste products of biological processes, including urine or feces, discharged from an organism's body.""^^xsd:string .

,Excreta material is a type of waste material, bodily fluid material, and something that is at least composed primarily of some excreta. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of excreta, consisting of matter that contains the waste products of biological processes, including urine or feces, discharged from an organism's body.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of bile, a bodily fluid consisting of a bitter, yellow or green alkaline fluid secreted by hepatocytes from the liver of most vertebrates. In many species, bile is stored in the gallbladder between meals and upon eating is discharged into the duodenum where the bile aids the process of digestion of lipids.""^^xsd:string

,Bile material is a type of bodily fluid material and is also a type of something that is at least composed primarily of some bile. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of bile, a bodily fluid consisting of a bitter, yellow or green alkaline fluid secreted by hepatocytes from the liver of most vertebrates. In many species, bile is stored in the gallbladder between meals and upon eating is discharged into the duodenum where the bile aids the process of digestion of lipids. Additionally, bile material is related to the synonym gall.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of aqueous humour, a bodily fluid consisting of a thick watery substance that fills the space between the lens and the cornea.""^^xsd:string .

,Aqueous humour material is a type of bodily fluid material and also a type of substance that is at least composed primarily of some aqueous humor of the eyeball. It is defined as a bodily fluid material that is composed primarily of aqueous humour, which is a bodily fluid consisting of a thick watery substance filling the space between the lens and the cornea.",3,True

:has_definition ""An excreta material which is composed primarily of sweat, an excreta consisting primarily of water as well as a smaller amount of sodium chloride that is excreted by the sweat glands in the skin of mammals.""^^xsd:string .

,Sweat material, a type of excreta material, is defined as an excreta material primarily composed of sweat. Sweat, an excreta consisting primarily of water along with a smaller amount of sodium chloride, is excreted by the sweat glands in the skin of mammals.",2,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of chyme, a bodily fluid consisting of a liquid substance found in the stomach before passing through the pyloric valve and entering the duodenum. It results from the mechanical and chemical breakdown of a bolus and consists of partially digested food, water, hydrochloric acid, and various digestive enzymes.""^^xsd:string

,Chyme material is a type of bodily fluid material that is primarily composed of chyme. It is defined as a bodily fluid material consisting of a liquid substance found in the stomach before it passes through the pyloric valve and enters the duodenum. This material results from the mechanical and chemical breakdown of a bolus and includes partially digested food, water, hydrochloric acid, and various digestive enzymes. Furthermore, chyme material is exactly synonymous with chymus.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of blood plasma, a bodily fluid that comprises the liquid component of blood, in which the blood cells are suspended. It makes up about 55% of total blood volume.""^^xsd:string .

,Blood plasma material is a type of bodily fluid material and is primarily composed of blood plasma. It is defined as a bodily fluid material that comprises the liquid component of blood, where the blood cells are suspended, making up about 55% of the total blood volume.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of ear wax, a bodily fluid consisting of a yellowish, waxy substance secreted in the ear canal of humans and many other mammals. It plays an important role in the human ear canal, assisting in cleaning and lubrication, and also provides some protection from bacteria, fungi, and insects.""^^xsd:string

,Ear wax material is a type of bodily fluid material defined as a bodily fluid material primarily composed of ear wax—a yellowish, waxy substance secreted in the ear canal of humans and many other mammals. It plays a crucial role in the human ear canal by assisting in cleaning and lubrication, and it also provides some protection from bacteria, fungi, and insects. Additionally, ear wax material is exactly synonymous with cerumen material.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of cerebrospinal fluid, a clear bodily fluid that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain. CSF is a clear bodily fluid that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain.""^^xsd:string

,Cerebrospinal fluid material is a type of bodily fluid material and is also referred to as a type of caro 0000000. It is specifically a type of material that is composed primarily of cerebrospinal fluid, a clear bodily fluid occupying the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain. Cerebrospinal fluid material is defined as a bodily fluid material primarily composed of cerebrospinal fluid. It has an exact synonym, CSF material, and a related synonym, Liquor cerebrospinalis.",6,True
:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of chyle, a bodily fluid consisting of a milky fluid consisting of lymph and emulsified fats
column2: formed in the small intestine during digestion of ingested fats.""^^xsd:string .

column1: ,Chyle material is a type of caro 0000000, bodily fluid material, and something that is at least primarily composed of chyle. It is defined as a bodily fluid material primarily consisting of chyle, which is a milky fluid made up of lymph and emulsified fats formed in the small intestine during the digestion of ingested fats.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of breast milk, is a bodily fluid produced that is secreted from two milk-secreting glandular organs on a female's chest.""^^xsd:string .

,Breast milk material is a type of bodily fluid material that is primarily composed of milk. It is defined as a bodily fluid produced and secreted from two milk-secreting glandular organs on a female's chest.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000032,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of vitreous humor, a bodily fluid consisting of a clear gel that fills the space between the lens and the retina of the eyeball of humans and other vertebrates.""^^xsd:string

,Vitreous humor material is a type of bodily fluid material and is also known as vitreous humour material. It is defined as a bodily fluid material composed primarily of vitreous humor, which is a clear gel filling the space between the lens and the retina of the eyeball in humans and other vertebrates. This material can be described as something that is at least primarily composed of vitreous humor.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of a pleural effusion, a bodily fluid that is produced in excess and accumulates in the pleural cavity, the fluid-filled space that surrounds the lungs. Excessive amounts of such fluid can impair breathing by limiting the expansion of the lungs during inhalation.""^^xsd:string .

,Pleural effusion material is a type of bodily fluid material that is primarily composed of pleural effusion, which is a bodily fluid produced in excess and accumulates in the pleural cavity, the fluid-filled space that surrounds the lungs. Excessive amounts of such fluid can impair breathing by limiting the expansion of the lungs during inhalation.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of a volume of tears, a bodily fluid consisting of a drop of the clear salty liquid secreted by glands (lacrimal glands) in the eyes. Tears wet the membrane covering the eye and help rid the eye of irritating substances.""^^xsd:string .

,Tear material is a type of bodily fluid material, defined as a bodily fluid material primarily composed of a volume of tears. Tears are a clear salty liquid secreted by glands in the eyes known as lacrimal glands. They serve to wet the membrane covering the eye and help rid the eye of irritating substances.",2,True
:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of an oronasal secretion, a bodily fluid secreted from the body via the mouth or nose.""^^xsd:string .

,Oronasal secretion material is a type of bodily fluid material, defined as a bodily fluid material that is primarily composed of an oronasal secretion. This secretion is a bodily fluid secreted from the body via the mouth or nose. Additionally, oronasal secretion material is something that is at least composed primarily of some oronasal secretion.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of saliva, a slightly alkaline secretion of water, mucin, protein, salts, and often a starch-splitting enzyme (as ptyalin) that is secreted into the mouth by salivary glands, lubricates ingested food, and often begins the breakdown of starches.""^^xsd:string .

,Saliva material is a type of bodily fluid material and is also defined as a type of material that is composed primarily of saliva. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which is primarily made up of saliva, a slightly alkaline secretion consisting of water, mucin, protein, salts, and often a starch-splitting enzyme known as ptyalin. This secretion is produced in the mouth by the salivary glands, serves to lubricate ingested food, and often initiates the breakdown of starches.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of sebum, an oily bodily fluid secreted from the sebaceous glads that is made of fat (lipids) and the debris of dead fat-producing cells. In the glands, sebum is produced within specialized cells and is released as these cells burst. Sebum acts to protect and waterproof hair and skin, and keep them from becoming dry, brittle and cracked. It can also inhibit the growth of microorganisms on skin.""^^xsd:string .

,Sebum material is a type of bodily fluid material, primarily composed of sebum, an oily substance secreted from the sebaceous glands. It consists of fat (lipids) and debris from dead fat-producing cells. Within the glands, sebum is produced by specialized cells and is released when these cells burst. The function of sebum is to protect and waterproof hair and skin, preventing them from becoming dry, brittle, and cracked. Additionally, it can inhibit the growth of microorganisms on the skin.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of pus, a bodily fluid consisting of a whitish-yellow or yellow substance produced during inflammatory responses of the body that can be found in regions of pyogenic bacterial infections. Pus is produced from the dead and living cells which travel into the intercellular spaces around the affected cells.""^^xsd:string .

,Pus material is a type of bodily fluid material, primarily composed of pus. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which essentially consists of a whitish-yellow or yellow substance. This substance is generated during the body's inflammatory responses and is prevalent in areas of pyogenic bacterial infections. The composition of pus includes dead and living cells that migrate into the spaces around the cells affected by the infection.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of synovial fluid, a bodily fluid secreted by the synovial membrane into the joint cavity to form a thin layer at the surface of cartilage.""^^xsd:string .

,Synovial fluid material is a type of caro 0000000, bodily fluid material, and something that is at least composed primarily of synovial fluid. It is defined as a bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of synovial fluid, a bodily fluid secreted by the synovial membrane into the joint cavity to form a thin layer at the surface of cartilage.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of mucus, a bodily fluid consisting of a slippery secretion of the lining of the mucous membranes in the body. It is a viscous colloid containing antiseptic enzymes (such as lysozyme) and immunoglobulins. Mucus is produced by goblet cells in the mucous membranes that cover the surfaces of the membranes. It is made up of mucins and inorganic salts suspended in water.""^^xsd:string .

,Mucus material is a type of bodily fluid that is primarily composed of mucus. It is defined as a bodily fluid material consisting of a slippery secretion from the lining of the mucous membranes in the body. This viscous colloid features antiseptic enzymes, such as lysozyme, and immunoglobulins, produced by goblet cells in the mucous membranes covering the surfaces of these membranes. Its composition includes mucins and inorganic salts suspended in water.",3,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of lymph, a bodily fluid consisting of a usually clear coagulable fluid that passes from intercellular spaces of body tissue into the lymphatic vessels, is discharged into the blood by way of the thoracic duct and right lymphatic duct, and resembles blood plasma in containing white blood cells and especially lymphocytes but normally few red blood cells and no platelets.""^^xsd:string .

,Lymph material is a type of bodily fluid material that is composed primarily of lymph, which is a clear, coagulable fluid. This fluid passes from the intercellular spaces of body tissues into the lymphatic vessels and is discharged into the blood via the thoracic duct and right lymphatic duct. It resembles blood plasma in that it contains white blood cells and especially lymphocytes, but it normally has few red blood cells and no platelets.",4,True

:has_definition ""A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of interstitial fluid, a bodily fluid consisting of a solution which bathes and surrounds the cells of multicellular animals. It is the main component of the extracellular fluid, which also includes plasma and transcellular fluid.""^^xsd:string

,Interstitital fluid material is a type of bodily fluid material and is primarily composed of interstitial fluid, which is itself a type of bodily fluid. It is defined as a bodily fluid material composed primarily of interstitial fluid, a solution that bathes and surrounds the cells of multicellular animals and is the main component of the extracellular fluid, which also includes plasma and transcellular fluid. Additionally, interstitial fluid material is exactly synonymous with intercellular fluid material and tissue fluid material.",5,True

:has_definition ""A biological product is an environmental substrate comprised of any virus, therapeutic serum, toxin, antitoxin, or analogous product available to prevent, treat or cure diseases or injuries in man.""^^xsd:string .

,A biological product, which is a type of manufactured product, is defined as an environmental substrate comprised of any virus, therapeutic serum, toxin, antitoxin, or analogous product available to prevent, treat, or cure diseases or injuries in humans.",2,True

:has_definition ""Siliceous ooze is a marine sediment composed of the debris of plankton with silica shells, such as diatoms and radiolaria. This ooze is limited to areas with high biological productivity, such as the polar oceans, and upwelling zones near the equator. The least common type of sediment, it covers only 15% of the ocean floor. It accumulates at a slower rate than calcareous ooze: 0.2-1 cm / 1000 yr.""^^xsd:string .

,Siliceous ooze is a type of biogenous sediment with a specific definition: it is a marine sediment composed of the debris of plankton with silica shells, such as diatoms and radiolaria. This particular ooze is confined to regions with high biological productivity, including the polar oceans and upwelling zones near the equator. Representing the least common type of sediment, siliceous ooze encompasses merely 15% of the ocean floor and accumulates at a slower pace than calcareous ooze, with a rate of 0.2-1 cm per 1000 years.",2,True

:has_definition ""Red clay, also known as pelagic clay, accumulates in the deepest and most remote areas of the ocean. Containing less than 30% biogenic material, its composition is a varied mix of very fine quartz and clay minerals, authigenic deposits precipitated directly from seawater, and micrometeorites. Though called \""red\"" because it sometimes takes the color of oxidized iron minerals, it is usually brownish in color. Its ultimate origin is uncertain, but red clay seems to be mostly derived from distant rivers, and windblown dust. Covering 38% of the ocean floor, it accumulates more slowly than any other sediment type, at only 0.1-0.5 cm / 1000 yr.""^^xsd:string .

,Red clay is identified as a type of biogenous sediment. It is defined as Red clay, also recognized as pelagic clay, which predominantly settles in the deepest and most isolated regions of the ocean. This sediment is characterized by containing less than 30% biogenic material. Its composition encompasses a diverse mixture that includes very fine quartz and clay minerals, authigenic deposits that precipitate directly from seawater, and micrometeorites. Despite its name, ""red"" clay, which is attributed to the coloration from oxidized iron minerals, it predominantly exhibits a brownish hue. The precise origins of red clay remain somewhat ambiguous
column2: however, it is largely believed to be derived from distant rivers and windblown dust. Remarkably, red clay covers 38% of the ocean floor, yet it accumulates at a slower rate than any other sediment type, with a rate of only 0.1-0.5 cm per 1000 years.",2,True

column1: :has_definition ""Calcareous ooze is a marine sediment composed primarily of the shells--also known as tests--of foraminifera, coccolithophores, and pteropods. This is the most common pelagic sediment by area, covering 48% of the world ocean's floor. This type of ooze is limited to depths above the Carbonate Compensation Depth at time of burial. It accumulates more rapidly than any other pelagic sediment type, with a rate that varies from 0.3 - 5 cm / 1000 yr.""^^xsd:string .

,Calcareous ooze is a type of biogenous sediment, which is defined as a marine sediment primarily composed of the shells, also known as tests, of foraminifera, coccolithophores, and pteropods. This form of sediment is the most common pelagic sediment by area, covering 48% of the world ocean's floor. Calcareous ooze is limited to depths above the Carbonate Compensation Depth at the time of burial and accumulates more rapidly than any other type of pelagic sediment, with a rate that varies from 0.3 - 5 cm per 1000 years.",2,True
:has_definition ""Food material which can be used to meet nutritional requirements of animals, particularly livestock such as cattle, goats, sheep, horses, chickens and pigs.""^^xsd:string

,Animal feed, which is a type of food material, is defined as food material that can be used to meet the nutritional requirements of animals, particularly livestock such as cattle, goats, sheep, horses, chickens, and pigs. It is also related to the synonym fodder.",3,True
:has_definition ""Contaminated animal feed is an animal feed that has become contaminated with or come contact with microorganisms or toxic chemicals.""^^xsd:string .

,Contaminated animal feed is a type of animal feed defined as animal feed that has become contaminated with or come into contact with microorganisms or toxic chemicals.,2,True

:has_definition ""A skin obtained from animals for human use typically from deer or cattle sources used to produce leather, shoes, fashion accessories, musical instruments.""^^xsd:string .

:has_definition ""Food material which can be used to meet nutritional requirements of plants.""^^xsd:string .

,Plant feed is a type of food material which is defined as food material that can be used to meet the nutritional requirements of plants.,2,True

,Paraffin wax, which is a type of wax, is defined as a white or colorless soft solid that can be derived from petroleum, coal, or oil shale. It consists of a mixture of hydrocarbon molecules containing between twenty and forty carbon atoms.",2,True
:has_definition ""An organic-rich fine-grained sedimentary rock containing kerogen from which liquid hydrocarbons called shale oil can be produced.""

,Oil shale is a type of shale and has the definition of being an organic-rich fine-grained sedimentary rock containing kerogen from which liquid hydrocarbons called shale oil can be produced. Additionally, oil shale has an exact synonym, which is kerogen shale.",3,True

,Zinc chloride fume is a type of fume that is the same as something which intersects with a fume and also is a type of entity that at least has part some zinc dichloride.,3,True

envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000123,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:has_definition ""Any liquid, liquefiable, or mastic composition that, after application to a substrate in a thin layer, converts to a solid film. It is most commonly used to protect, color, or provide texture to objects."" .

,Paint is a type of anthropogenic and liquid environmental material. It is defined as any liquid, liquefiable, or mastic composition that, after application to a substrate in a thin layer, converts to a solid film. It is most commonly used to protect, color, or provide texture to objects.",3,True

,Lead paint is defined as paint that contains lead. It is a type of paint that intersects with something that is paint and also something that at least has some part of a lead molecular entity. Furthermore, lead paint is classified as a type of entity that at least partially consists of some lead molecular entity.",4,True
:has_definition ""A planned process that is the movement of people, animals and goods from one location to another."" .

,Transportation is defined as a planned process that involves the movement of people, animals, and goods from one location to another, and it falls under the category of material transport processes.",2,True
:has_definition ""the residue powder that is derived from the combustion of wood."" .

,Wood ash is defined as the residue powder derived from the combustion of wood and is the same as something that intersects between ash and something that at least derives from some wood. It is a type of ash and also a type of something that at least derives from some wood. Moreover, wood ash is a type of something that is at least an output of something that intersects between a combustion process and something that at least has wood as an input.",5,True
:has_definition ""Ash that is produced from the burning of coal.""

,Coal ash is the same as something that is both ash and something that at least derives from some coal. It is a type of ash and also a type of something that at least derives from some coal.
