Coal ash is defined as ash that is produced from the burning of coal and has the exact synonym ""coal combustion residuals.""",6,True
:has_definition ""A very fine, powdery material composed mostly of silica made from the burning of finely ground coal in a boiler."" .
,Fly ash, a type of coal ash, is defined as a very fine, powdery material composed mostly of silica made from the burning of finely ground coal in a boiler.",2,True
:has_definition ""a coarse, angular ash particle that is too large to be carried up into the smoke stacks so it forms in the bottom of the coal furnace."" .
,Bottom ash is a type of coal ash characterized as a coarse, angular ash particle that is too large to be carried up into the smoke stacks, thus forming at the bottom of the coal furnace.",2,True
:has_definition ""molten bottom ash from slag tap and cyclone type furnaces that turns into pellets that have a smooth glassy appearance after it is cooled with water."" .

,Boiler slag, a type of coal ash, is defined as molten bottom ash from slag tap and cyclone type furnaces. It turns into pellets with a smooth, glassy appearance after being cooled with water.",2,True

:has_definition ""a material leftover from the process of reducing sulfur dioxide emissions from a coal-fired boiler that can be a wet sludge consisting of calcium sulfite or calcium sulfate or a dry powered material that is a mixture of sulfites and sulfates."" .

,Flue gas desulfurization material, a type of coal ash, is defined as a material left over from the process of reducing sulfur dioxide emissions from a coal-fired boiler. It can either be a wet sludge consisting of calcium sulfite or calcium sulfate, or a dry powdered material that is a mixture of sulfites and sulfates.",2,True
:has_definition ""A human construction which serves as a memorial.""@en .
,A constructed monument is a type of human construction that serves as a memorial, which is broadly synonymous with the term monument.",3,True
:has_definition ""A human construction which is used to initiate and control a fission nuclear chain reaction or nuclear fusion reactions."" .

,A nuclear reactor is a type of human construction that is capable of generating energy through the intersection of anthropogenic generation of energy and the realization of nuclear energy. It is defined as a human construction used to initiate and control a fission nuclear chain reaction or nuclear fusion reactions.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000134,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A nuclear reactor which uses a neutron moderator to slow neutrons until they approach the average kinetic energy of the surrounding particles.""

,A thermal nuclear reactor is a type of nuclear power reactor, which is defined as a nuclear reactor that uses a neutron moderator to slow neutrons until they approach the average kinetic energy of the surrounding particles. It is also exactly synonymous with the term ""thermal reactor.""",3,True
:has_definition ""A nuclear reactor in which the fission chain reaction is sustained by fast neutrons.""

,A fast neutron reactor, which is a type of nuclear power reactor, is defined as a nuclear reactor in which the fission chain reaction is sustained by fast neutrons. It is also exactly synonymous with the term ""fast reactor.""",3,True
:has_definition ""A nuclear reactor which serves primarily as a neutron source for purposes other than power.""

,A research nuclear reactor is a type of nuclear reactor which serves primarily as a neutron source for purposes other than power, distinguishing itself from a nuclear power reactor. This type of reactor is also exactly synonymous with non-power reactor, nuclear test reactor, and test reactor.",6,True
:has_definition ""A nuclear reactor which is used as a source of power.""
,A nuclear power reactor is a type of nuclear reactor, which is defined as a nuclear reactor used as a source of power. It is also exactly synonymous with the term ""power reactor.""",3,True
:has_definition ""Soil which is located in a mangrove biome.""

,Mangrove biome soil is a type of soil that is located in a mangrove biome, and it is the same as something that intersects with soil and something that is at least located in some mangrove biome. This type of soil is defined as soil which is located in a mangrove biome and has the exact synonym ""mangrove soil.""",5,True

,Fluid environmental material is the same as the union of gaseous environmental material, plasma, and liquid environmental material. It is a type of environmental material with the definition of being a liquid or a gas. Furthermore, fluid environmental material has a narrow synonym: fluid.",4,True
:has_definition ""A human construction which is used to process materials into forms that have increased value or utility in downstream processes."" .

,A refinery is defined as a human construction used to process materials into forms that have increased value or utility in downstream processes. It falls under the category of things that are at least capable of some refinement process. Essentially, a refinery is the same as something that intersects the characteristics of being a human construction and being capable of at least some refinement process.",4,True
:has_definition ""A refinery which is capable of processing petroleum oil.""

,A petroleum oil refinery, which is exactly synonymous with an oil refinery, is defined as a refinery capable of processing petroleum oil. It is identified as a type of refinery that aligns with entities capable of undergoing a refinement process specifically designed for inputs including petroleum. This definition encapsulates the essence of a petroleum oil refinery by highlighting its operational capability and its essential input, petroleum, without losing the nuanced connection to the broader category of refineries that share these core characteristics.",5,True
:has_definition ""A refinery which is capable of processing raw sugar. Raw sugar is processed from cane or beets into white refined sugar."" .

,A sugar refinery is defined as a refinery that is capable of processing raw sugar, transforming it from cane or beets into white refined sugar. It falls under the category of refineries that are at least capable of undergoing a refinement process and that specifically have sugar as an input. Essentially, a sugar refinery is synonymous with any entity that is both a refinery and is capable of engaging in a refinement process that involves sugar as an essential input. Additionally, a sugar refinery is recognized as a type of refinery specialized in the refinement process related to sugar input.",4,True

:has_definition ""A refinery which is capable of processing natural gas. Natural-gas processing encompasses a range of industrial processes designed to purify raw natural gas by removing impurities, contaminants and higher molecular mass hydrocarbons to produce what is known as pipeline quality dry natural gas"" .

,A natural gas processing plant is essentially a refinery specifically designed for processing natural gas. It stands as a type of entity that intersects the capabilities of a refinery with that of an entity capable of undertaking a refinement process, particularly one that requires natural gas as an input. Moreover, the natural gas processing plant is defined as a refinery adept at processing natural gas. This processing encompasses a variety of industrial procedures aimed at purifying raw natural gas. The purification process involves removing impurities, contaminants, and higher molecular mass hydrocarbons to yield what is termed as pipeline quality dry natural gas.",4,True
:has_definition ""A planned process which has the intention of producing, consuming, or transforming materials via the execution of chemical reactions.""

,A chemical engineering process is a type of planned process, defined as a planned process with the intention of producing, consuming, or transforming materials through the execution of chemical reactions. It is also exactly synonymous with industrial chemical processing.",3,True
:has_definition ""A planned material transformation process which takes as input a material and removes impurities.""

,The refinement process, which is a type of chemical engineering process, is defined as a planned material transformation process that takes a material as input and removes impurities. It is also exactly synonymous with refining.",3,True
:has_definition ""A chemical engineering process that produces ammonia en masse via artificial nitrogen fixation.""

,The Haber Bosch process is a type of chemical engineering process that specifically involves the input of dinitrogen and outputs ammonia. It is defined as a chemical engineering process that produces ammonia en masse via artificial nitrogen fixation. Additionally, the Haber Bosch process is exactly synonymous with the Haber process.",5,True
:has_definition ""A chemical engineering process which generates hydrogen gas."" .
,The hydrogen production process is a type of chemical engineering process, defined as a chemical engineering process that generates hydrogen gas.",2,True
:has_definition ""A mineral deposit that contains uranium ore.""

,A uranium deposit is defined as a mineral deposit that contains uranium ore, which is equivalent to the intersection of a mineral deposit and something that has at least some part uranium ore. Additionally, a uranium deposit is a type of mineral deposit and also a type of entity that has at least some part uranium ore. It is exactly synonymous with the term ""uranium ore deposit.""",5,True
:has_definition ""A uranium deposit where self-sustaining nuclear chain reactions have occurred."" .

,A natural nuclear fission reactor is a type of uranium deposit defined as a uranium deposit where self-sustaining nuclear chain reactions have occurred.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process in which includes the components of an environmental system as participants."" .

,The environmental system process is defined as a process that includes the components of an environmental system as participants. It is identified as equivalent to an intersection involving a process and something that, at a minimum, includes participants that are a union of environmental material, environmental systems, astronomical bodies, astronomical objects, and parts of an astronomical body. Furthermore, the environmental system process is categorized as a type of process and also as a type of entity that necessarily involves participants from a collective group comprising environmental materials, environmental systems, astronomical bodies, astronomical objects, and astronomical body parts.",4,True
:has_definition ""A type of land degradation in which terrestrial ecosystem becomes increasingly dry, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife."" .

,Desertification is the same as something that intersects land degradation and something that at least has an output of some desert area. It is a type of land degradation and also a type of something that at least has input some complement of the union of desert area and desert biome, as well as a type of something that at least has output some desert area. Furthermore, desertification is defined as a type of land degradation in which a terrestrial ecosystem becomes increasingly dry, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.",5,True

:has_definition ""A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water."" .

,Flooding is a type of water flow process characterized by several key aspects. It involves processes where there is an accumulation of materials and the transport of these materials, both of which necessarily include liquid water as a participant. This process not only involves water bodies but also impacts planetary landmasses. Flooding is defined as a general and temporary condition that leads to the partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas. This condition can arise from various sources, including the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, alongside the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters. Essentially, flooding represents a significant flow along a watercourse or a flow that causes inundation of lands not typically covered by water.",6,True
:has_definition ""A process which occurs within an atmosphere."" .

,An atmospheric process is defined as a process which occurs within an atmosphere. It shares the same characteristics as processes that are at the intersection of environmental system processes and processes that at least occur in some atmosphere. Furthermore, an atmospheric process is categorized as a type of environmental system process and also as a type of process that at least occurs in some atmosphere.",4,True

:has_definition ""A process by which thermal radiation from a planetary surface is absorbed by atmospheric greenhouse gases, and is re-radiated in all directions. Since part of this re-radiation is back towards the surface and the lower atmosphere, it results in an elevation of the average surface temperature above what it would be in the absence of the gases."" .

,The greenhouse effect is a type of atmospheric process, which is defined as a process by which thermal radiation from a planetary surface is absorbed by atmospheric greenhouse gases and is re-radiated in all directions. Since part of this re-radiation is back towards the surface and the lower atmosphere, it results in an elevation of the average surface temperature above what it would be in the absence of the gases.",2,True
:has_definition ""A process which diminishes the functioning of an ecosystem located on land."" .

,Land degradation is a type of ecosystem process that is part of some land consumption process and involves terrestrial biomes as well as planetary landmasses. It is defined as a process which diminishes the functioning of an ecosystem located on land.,5,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500007,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process which consists of all photosynthesis processes instantiated in an ecosystem."" .

,Ecosystem-wide photosynthesis is identified as a type of ecosystem process, and it is also recognized as a type of hydrological process. This process is categorized under something that at least includes a part of photosynthesis. Furthermore, ecosystem-wide photosynthesis is defined as a type of process that requires as input a combination of carbon dioxide and liquid water, wherein the latter also plays the role of an electron donor. As for its output, it produces a combination of dioxygen and carbohydrate. Moreover, ecosystem-wide photosynthesis is defined as a process which encompasses all photosynthesis processes that occur within an ecosystem.",6,True
:has_definition ""A process which consists of all respiration processes instantiated in an ecosystem."" .

,Ecosystem-wide respiration is a type of environmental system process that encompasses all respiration processes instantiated within an ecosystem. It is described as a process that, at the very least, involves some form of cellular respiration. Furthermore, ecosystem-wide respiration requires inputs that are intersections of chemical entities with specific roles, including those that act as electron acceptors and those that serve as nutrients. Additionally, this process produces ATP as an output.",6,True
:has_definition ""A biogeochemical process during which one or more chemical compounds are sequentially converted into a series of related compounds in a regularly repeating, periodic fashion."" .

,Biogeochemical cycling is a type of biogeochemical process that is defined as a biogeochemical process during which one or more chemical compounds are sequentially converted into a series of related compounds in a regularly repeating, periodic fashion.",2,True
:has_definition ""A biogeochemical cycle which has carbon-bearing chemical entities as participants.""

,Carbon cycling is synonymous with the carbon cycle, and it is defined as a biogeochemical cycle which involves carbon-bearing chemical entities as participants. This process is equivalent to something that is at the intersection of biogeochemical cycling and processes that at least have an input of some carbon atom. Furthermore, carbon cycling is a specific type of biogeochemical cycling and also falls under the category of processes that at least involve a participant that is at the intersection of a chemical entity and entities that have at least a part of a carbon atom. Additionally, carbon cycling is characterized as a type of process that at least has an input of some carbon atom.",6,True
:has_definition ""Establishment of a new forest by seeding or planting of nonforested land."" .

,Afforestation is a type of planned revegetation and also a method that involves the establishment of a new forest by seeding or planting on nonforested land. It is characterized by processes that require an input, which complements the union of the forest biome and the forest ecosystem. Similarly, it produces an output that is a union of the forest biome and the forest ecosystem.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ecosystem process during which the flora and fauna belonging to a forest are removed or destroyed."" .

,Deforestation is categorized as an ecosystem process and is defined as an ecosystem process during which the flora and fauna belonging to a forest are removed or destroyed. It serves as a process that, at the very least, takes inputs from something that encompasses the union of forested areas and forest biomes. Additionally, deforestation outputs something that is the complement of the union of forested areas and forest biomes. Moreover, deforestation is broadly synonymous with both clearance and clearing.",6,True
:has_definition ""The planting of trees in areas in where forests have previously been cleared."" .

,Reforestation is a type of planned revegetation and also a type of activity that involves at least some expansion of forest areas. It is defined as the planting of trees in areas where forests have previously been cleared.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500014,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

,Forest process is the same as something that intersects with an ecosystem process and something that at least has a participant in some forested area. Additionally, forest process is a type of ecosystem process and also a type of something that at least has a participant in some forested area.",3,True

,Forest area expansion shares the same characteristics as something that intersects with an ecosystem process and something that at least results in the expansion of some forested area. It is categorized as a type of ecosystem process. Moreover, forest area expansion is also identified as a type of process that at least encompasses some aspect of afforestation and leads to the expansion of some forested area.",4,True

:has_definition ""A process during which the populations in a community of algae in a marine or freshwater ecosystem undergo rapid growth, resulting in high concentrations of algal cells that occur only periodically and briefly in that ecosystem, relative to their concentrations through the majority of the planetary orbital period."" .

,The algal bloom process is a type of ecosystem process that occurs in aquatic environments. It results in the proliferation of algae and involves the participation of algal blooms. This process is defined as a period during which the populations of algae in a marine or freshwater ecosystem experience rapid growth. This results in high concentrations of algal cells that occur only periodically and briefly in that ecosystem, compared to their concentrations through the majority of the planetary orbital period.",5,True

,alga is a type of cellular organisms.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500021,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process during which the rapid growth of algal populations that result in an algal bloom ceases, and cell densities begin to fall due to death, predation, and transport."" .

,Algal bloom collapse is a type of ecosystem process and also a type of process that at least ends some algal bloom process. It is defined as a process during which the rapid growth of algal populations that result in an algal bloom ceases, and cell densities begin to fall due to death, predation, and transport.",3,True
,The algal bloom process phase is a type of ecosystem process and is also considered to be a part of, or at least partially involved in, some algal bloom processes.",2,True
:has_definition ""A process during which the algal cells constituting an algal bloom produce biomass from abiotic components during photosynthesis."" .

,Algal production is a type of ecosystem process, and it is also a part of some algal bloom processes as well as photosynthesis. Furthermore, it is defined as a process during which the algal cells that make up an algal bloom produce biomass from abiotic components through photosynthesis.",4,True

,accumulation of toxins from algal bloom process is a type of algal bloom process phase.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500025,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

,degradation of toxins from algal bloom process is a type of algal bloom process phase.,1,False
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500026,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process during which humans apply technology to alter the magnitude, duration, rate, or impact of an environmental process."" .

,Anthropogenic modulatory intervention process is defined as a process during which humans apply technology to alter the magnitude, duration, rate, or impact of an environmental process. This process is equivalent to an intersection of a planned process and something that at least regulates processual environmental system processes, as well as something that at least has humans as its causal agents. Specifically, it is characterized as a type of planned process, a type of process that regulates environmental system processes to some extent, and a type of process that necessarily involves humans as causal agents.",5,True
:has_definition ""An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans."" .

,Anthropogenic environmental processes are defined as environmental processes driven by the action of humans. They are a type of environmental system process and also a type of process that has Homo sapiens as a causal agent. Moreover, anthropogenic environmental processes are equivalent to the intersection of environmental system processes and processes that have at least one Homo sapiens as a causal agent.",4,True

:has_definition ""An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove environmental material from one part of a planet's crust, transporting it to another location where it is deposited."" .

,Planetary erosion is a type of erosion that is defined as the action of exogenic processes, such as water flow or wind, which remove environmental material from one part of a planet's crust and transport it to another location where it is deposited.",2,True
:has_definition ""An erosional process in which bedrock is converted from its solid form into a solute by the action of some solvent."" .

,Bedrock dissolution is a type of planetary erosion and it is also a process where at least some bedrock participates. Additionally, bedrock dissolution involves the participation of something that is both a chemical entity and holds the role of a solvent. It is defined as an erosional process in which bedrock is converted from its solid form into a solute by the action of some solvent.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which chemicals that are involved in natural ecosystem processes are transported or transformed, and which impact the activity of biological entities"" .

,A biogeochemical process is a type of environmental system process that encompasses biological processes, involves chemical entities, and engages the natural environment as participants. It is defined as a process during which chemicals involved in natural ecosystem processes are transported or transformed, impacting the activity of biological entities.",5,True
:has_definition ""An environmental process which has water - in any of its states - as a participant."" .

,The hydrological process is defined as an environmental process that involves water, whether it be in the form of liquid water, water vapor, or water ice, as a participant. This process is equivalent to the intersection of environmental system processes and processes that include, at the very least, one participant that is either liquid water, water vapor, or water ice. Additionally, the hydrological process is categorized under environmental system processes and is a type of process that involves, at a minimum, a participant that is a union of water, water vapor, or water ice. Essentially, the hydrological process encompasses any environmental system process that involves water in any of its states.",5,True
:has_definition ""A planned process during which human agents establish plant communities in ecosystems which have previously been, partially or wholly, stripped of existing plant communities."" .

,Planned revegetation is a type of active ecosystem management process and is also a type of process that at least results in some vegetated area. It is defined as a planned process during which human agents establish plant communities in ecosystems that have previously been, partially or wholly, stripped of existing plant communities.",3,True
:has_definition ""Evapotranspiration is the sum of evaporation and plant transpiration from the Earth's land and ocean surface to the atmosphere."" .

,Evapotranspiration is a type of water flow process and it is a type of something that at least has part some intersection of hydrological evaporation and transpiration. Furthermore, evapotranspiration is defined as the sum of evaporation and plant transpiration from the Earth's land and ocean surface to the atmosphere.",3,True

:has_definition ""Evaporation is a form of vaporisation which occurs when a portion of the surface layer of a liquid in contact with a gaseous material, which is not saturated with the evaporating substance, vaporises."" .

,Evaporation is a type of vaporization that involves a process occurring at the surface layer of a liquid, which primarily consists of environmental material having the quality of a liquid. The definition of evaporation is as follows: Evaporation is a form of vaporization that occurs when a portion of the surface layer of a liquid in contact with a gaseous material, which is not saturated with the evaporating substance, vaporizes.",3,True
:has_definition ""Transpiration is the process of water movement through a plant and its evaporation from aerial parts of that plant, such as from leaves but also from stems and flowers."" .

,Transpiration is defined as the process of water movement through a plant and its evaporation from aerial parts of that plant, such as from leaves but also from stems and flowers. It is a type of water cooling and also a type of process that involves, at least in part, some evaporation.",3,True
:has_definition ""An environmental system process that results in the introduction of contaminants into an environment.""

,Environmental pollution is a type of environmental system process. It is characterized by being a process that outputs substances which are both environmental materials and have increased levels of chemical entities that play the role of environmental contaminants. Furthermore, environmental pollution is defined as an environmental system process that results in the introduction of contaminants into an environment. Additionally, environmental pollution is exactly synonymous with pollution.",4,True
:has_definition ""A pollution process during which particulates or other contaminants are released into a portion of air."" .

,Air pollution is defined as a pollution process during which particulates or other contaminants are released into a portion of air. It is identified as the same as something that intersects with both something that is a type of environmental pollution and something that occurs at least in some air. Furthermore, air pollution is categorized as a type of environmental pollution, as well as a type of phenomenon that occurs in some air. Additionally, it is a type of entity that at least has an input from something that intersects with something that is a part of the environmental system and something that has at least a part of the air. It is also described as a type of entity that at least produces an output of something that intersects with something that is a part of the environmental system and something that has at least a part of contaminated air.",6,True
:has_definition ""A pollution process during which contaminants are released into soil."" .

,Soil pollution is defined as a pollution process during which contaminants are released into the soil. It is a type of environmental pollution and occurs in soils, meaning it happens in environments where soil is a component. Specifically, soil pollution can be characterized by its relationship to systems where soil is a part, including those that involve environmental systems with soil as a part or where the output includes contaminated soil. This encompasses systems where the environmental system includes parts that are contaminated soil, highlighting the intersection of environmental pollution with occurrences in soil and the impact on environmental systems and their soil components.",7,True
:has_definition ""A pollution process during which contaminants are released into water."" .

,Water pollution is defined as a pollution process during which contaminants are released into water, and it is considered a type of environmental pollution. Specifically, water pollution is equivalent to something that intersects with environmental pollution and something that unions with a water body or at least occurs in some form of liquid water. Moreover, water pollution is categorized as a type of phenomenon that has, as an input, something that intersects with an environmental system and something that includes as a part some form of liquid water. Additionally, it is also seen as a type of occurrence that results in, as an output, something that intersects with an environmental system and involves as a part some form of contaminated water.",5,True
:has_definition ""A pollution process during which plastic contaminants are released into an environmental material."" .

,Plastic pollution is characterized as a form of environmental pollution that emerges when plastic contaminants are discharged into materials found in the environment. This specific type of pollution is essentially an intersection of increased levels of synthetic plastic and environmental contaminants impacting environmental materials. Essentially, plastic pollution is defined as the process through which plastic contaminants are released into an environmental material.",3,True
:has_definition ""An process in which environmental parameters and variables are continually assayed."" .

,Environmental monitoring is a type of planned process that involves the continuous assay of environmental parameters and variables. It is a process that necessarily involves at least one participant, which can be either an environmental material, an environmental system, or a part of an astronomical body. Additionally, this process requires a causal agent, specifically Homo sapiens, indicating that humans play a crucial role in environmental monitoring. Furthermore, environmental monitoring is broadly synonymous with the term ""monitoring,"" highlighting its general applicability in various contexts.",5,True
:has_definition ""A planned process during which the amount of pollutants released into an environmental system is regulated.""

,Pollution control is defined as a planned process during which the amount of pollutants released into an environmental system is regulated, and it is synonymous, albeit more narrowly, with pollution prevention. It is identified as a type of anthropogenic modulatory intervention process and also as a type that at least regulates the processual aspects of some environmental pollution. Additionally, pollution control is the same as something that intersects both something that is an anthropogenic modulatory intervention process and something that at least regulates the processual aspects of some environmental pollution.",5,True
:has_definition ""A monitoring process that assays the level of environmental pollutants to determine the presence of effect of environmental pollution."" .

,Pollution monitoring is equivalent to something that intersects environmental monitoring and something that is causally downstream of or within some environmental pollution. It is a specific type of environmental monitoring and also a type that is at least causally downstream of or within some environmental pollution. Furthermore, pollution monitoring is defined as a monitoring process that assays the level of environmental pollutants to determine the presence or effect of environmental pollution.",4,True
:has_definition ""A pollution process that results in increased levels of pollutants in an urban environment."" .

,Urban pollution is defined as a pollution process that results in increased levels of pollutants in an urban environment. It is synonymous with something that is an intersection of environmental pollution and something that occurs at least in some urban biome. Urban pollution is categorized as a type of environmental pollution and also as a type of occurrence that happens at least in some urban biome. Furthermore, it is a type of phenomenon that at least has input from some urban biome and is a type of event that at least generates output that is an intersection of an urban biome and something that includes a part of the intersection of environmental material with something that has increased levels of a chemical entity which also plays a role as an environmental contaminant.",6,True

:has_definition ""Partially compacted granular snow, which has undergone several cycles of melting and refreezing while being compacted, usually found on the atmosphere-exposed surface of a glacier.""

,Neve is a type of snow that is also known for being granular and derives from powdery snow. It is defined as partially compacted granular snow, which has undergone several cycles of melting and refreezing while being compacted, and is usually found on the atmosphere-exposed surface of a glacier. Additionally, neve has an exact synonym: névé.",5,True

:has_definition ""Granular snow which contains a proportion of fused granules formed through melting and re-thawing while being compacted by the weight of overlying material and which contains interconnected gaseous pores."" .

,Firn is a type of snow that possesses at least some granular quality. Additionally, firn is derived from a substance that is a combination of either neve or powdery snow. It is defined as granular snow containing a proportion of fused granules formed through melting and re-thawing, while being compacted by the weight of overlying material, and contains interconnected gaseous pores.",4,True

:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which recently precipitated, powdery snow transitions into firn or névé through compaction and/or through cycles of freezing and thawing."" .

,Nivation is a type of material transformation process that involves several key components and sequences in its operation. Initially, it is a process that necessitates at least a part of it being a compaction process. Additionally, nivation is characterized by being preceded by snowfall, highlighting its dependency on this weather phenomenon. The input for nivation is specifically powdery snow, setting the stage for its transformation. As for the output, nivation results in a substance that is a combination of névé and firn, which are stages in the snow-to-ice transformation process. The comprehensive definition of nivation encapsulates it as a material transformation process where recently precipitated, powdery snow undergoes a transition into firn or névé. This transition is facilitated through compaction and/or through cycles of freezing and thawing, illustrating the intricate and natural progression inherent in the nivation process.",6,True
:has_definition ""Any water ice that is part of a glacier."" .

,Glacial ice is the same as something that intersects between water ice and something that is at least part of some glacier. It is defined as any water ice that is part of a glacier. Furthermore, glacial ice is identified as a type of water ice, as well as a type of something that is at least part of some glacier.",4,True
:has_definition ""Glacial ice which contains material liberated during a glacial erosion process."" .

,Erosionally enriched glacial ice is a type of glacial ice, and it is also a type of erosionally enriched ice, as well as a type of substance that is at least an output of some glacial erosion process. It is defined as glacial ice which contains material liberated during a glacial erosion process.",4,True
:has_definition ""An erosion process during which the movement of a glacier across a terrestrial surface causes the removal of material from that surface."" .

,The glacial erosion process is a type of glacial process and also falls under the category of planetary erosion. It is characterized by the involvement of at least some glacier and some planetary landmass as participants. The definition of the glacial erosion process is an erosion process during which the movement of a glacier across a terrestrial surface causes the removal of material from that surface. Furthermore, glaciation is considered a broad synonym for the glacial erosion process.",6,True
:has_definition ""Water ice containing little to no air bubbles resulting in a reduction of internal light scattering and, given sufficient volume, a blue appearance."" .

,Blue ice is the same as something that intersects something that is ice and something that at least has the quality of being somewhat blue. It is a type of water ice and also a type of something that at least has some quality of being blue. Furthermore, blue ice is defined as water ice containing little to no air bubbles, resulting in a reduction of internal light scattering and, given sufficient volume, a blue appearance.",4,True
:has_definition ""A physical process during which atoms, molecules, or other consituents of a material entity are forced closer together."" .

,The compaction process is a type of environmental system process with the definition of being a physical process during which atoms, molecules, or other constituents of a material entity are forced closer together.",2,True
:has_definition ""A process during which the mass of one or more materials, present within a given site, increases."" .

,The material accumulation process is categorized under environmental system processes. It is identified as a process that concludes with the amalgamation of material transport and material transformation processes. Furthermore, this process is characterized by its output, which is the intersection of a material entity with an entity that possesses the quality of increased mass. The material accumulation process is defined as a process during which the mass of one or more materials present within a given site increases.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which material is displaced from its original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location."" .

,Material transport process falls under the category of environmental system processes. It is characterized as a process where the output involves a material entity that has been displaced, which essentially means that it possesses the quality of being moved from its original position. Additionally, the material transport process is defined as a process during which material is displaced from its original location and transported either to a new location or returned to the original location.",3,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which the mass of an existing ice mass increases."" .

,Ice gain is a type of ice accumulation process and is also known as a process where something, at least having some ice mass as a participant, occurs. It is defined as a material accumulation process during which the mass of an existing ice mass increases. Moreover, ice gain is broadly synonymous with both the accumulation of ice and ice accumulation.",5,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which the snow and ice constituting a glacier, and anything contained within it, is transported down a slope by gravitation.""

,The glacial transport process is a type of mass ice flow, a glacial process, and something that involves at least one glacier as a participant. It is defined as a material transport process during which the snow and ice constituting a glacier, along with anything contained within it, is transported down a slope by gravitation. This process is also exactly synonymous with glacial flow and glacial movement.",6,True
:has_definition ""A small glacier contained within a cirque basin."" .

,A cirque glacier is a type of glacier that is characterized by having a decreased size and being adjacent to a cirque. It is defined as a small glacier contained within a cirque basin.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000015,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A depression which is part of a planetary crust, is of geographic scale, and is partially or completely enclosed."" .

,A geographic basin is a type of depressed landform, which is part of a planetary crust and is of geographic scale. It is defined as a depression that is partially or completely enclosed and at least overlaps some parts of the planetary crust.",3,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a mass composed of one or more environmental materials, present within a given site, decreases."" .

,The material decumulation process is categorized as an environmental system process and is identified by a specific definition: it is a process during which a mass composed of one or more environmental materials, present within a given site, decreases. This process is characterized not only by its initiation phase, which involves the union of material transport and material transformation processes but also by its output. The output of the material decumulation process is notable for being the intersection of a material entity with any entity that has undergone a decrease in mass, indicating a reduction in the amount of material.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which the mass of ice constituting a glacier decreases."" .

,Glacial ice loss is a type of process that falls under several categories: it is an ice loss process, a glacial process, and a hydrological process. This process involves at least one participant, which can be a glacier or glacial ice. Glacial ice loss is defined as a process during which the mass of ice constituting a glacier decreases.",6,True
:has_definition ""A stream which is primarily composed of meltwater and which flows within a glacier or ice sheet."" .

,An englacial stream is a type of stream that is primarily composed of meltwater and flows within a glacier or ice sheet. It is a specific kind of stream that is at least partially surrounded by ice, including both ice sheets and glaciers. Additionally, it is characterized by having qualities that are specifically englacial. The definition of an englacial stream is a stream which flows within a glacier or ice sheet and is primarily composed of meltwater.",5,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which one or more environmental materials are transported by the action of wind.""

,The aeolian transport process, also known exactly as eolian or æolian, is a type of material transport process. This process is characterized by involving at least some atmospheric wind and includes the participation of one or more environmental materials. It is defined as a material transport process during which environmental materials are transported by the action of wind.",6,True
:has_definition ""Particulate environmental material which is composed primarily of carbon particles formed through the incomplete combustion of hydrocarbons.""@en .

,Soot is a type of particulate environmental material and is also a type of substance that is primarily composed of some organic molecular entity. It is defined as particulate environmental material composed primarily of carbon particles that are formed through the incomplete combustion of hydrocarbons.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000025,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""Water ice which contains material liberated during an erosion process."" .

,Erosionally enriched ice is a type of water ice that is defined as water ice containing material liberated during an erosion process.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000027,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

,Powdery snow is a type of snow defined as uncompacted snow containing trapped atmospheric gases.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000029,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A process during which the mass of ice constituting a glacier increases."" .

,Glacial ice gain is a type of glacial process and ice gain that involves at least one glacier as a participant. It is characterized by the input of substances including liquid water, snow, ice, neve, and firn, leading to the output of glacial ice. This process is defined as one during which the mass of ice constituting a glacier increases.",6,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a part of a glacier breaks away from the main mass.""

,The glacial ice calving process is a type of ice calving process, glacial process, and it is an activity that involves at least one glacier as a participant. This process is defined as a phenomenon during which a part of a glacier breaks away from the main mass. It is also exactly synonymous with glacier calving.",5,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a part of a glacier breaks away from the main mass as an iceberg.""

,The iceberg calving process is a type of glacial ice calving process, which is defined as a process during which a part of a glacier breaks away from the main mass as an iceberg. This process requires at least a glacier as its input and results in the creation of both a glacier and a marine iceberg. Furthermore, ""iceberg calving"" is an exact synonym for the iceberg calving process, while ""glacier calving"" is considered a related synonym.",7,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a part of an iceberg breaks away from the main mass."" .

,Calving of ice from an iceberg is a type of ice calving process and is defined as a process during which a part of an iceberg breaks away from the main mass. This process involves at least one participant, which is a marine iceberg, and results in the output of some ice mass.",4,True
:has_definition ""Sediment which has been transported through the marine water column, settling on the seafloor.""

,Marine sediment is identical to something that is a union of items that intersect both sediment and items that at least overlap with some marine water body, as well as items that intersect both sediment and items that are at least adjacent to some marine water body. Furthermore, marine sediment is classified as a type of sediment and also as a type of sediment that is at least adjacent to some marine water body. It is additionally categorized as a type of sediment that is at least an output of sedimentation in a water body. The definition of marine sediment is sediment that has been transported through the marine water column, settling on the seafloor. Moreover, marine sediment is exactly synonymous with marine sediments.",6,True

:has_definition ""Marine sediment soured from either terrestrial systems, marine organisms, seawater and or cosmogeneous sources, which is transported through the marine water column, and accumulates within shallow regions of the oceanic basin close to continents, such as the continental shelf, or continental slope.""

,Shallow marine sediment is a type of marine sediment that exists adjacent to a continental shelf and is an output of the intersection between sedimentation in a water body and processes occurring in the neritic pelagic zone biome. It is defined as marine sediment sourced from terrestrial systems, marine organisms, seawater, or cosmogenous sources. This sediment is transported through the marine water column and accumulates within shallow regions of the oceanic basin close to continents, such as the continental shelf or continental slope. Shallow marine sediment is also exactly synonymous with shallow marine sediments and is relatedly referred to as neritic marine sediment.",6,True
:has_definition ""A water body which is located in a depression within the surface of a glacier.""

,A supraglacial lake is a type of lake that is at least adjacent to some glacier and is defined as a water body located in a depression within the surface of a glacier. It is also exactly synonymous with supraglacial lakes.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000036,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which solid particles are pulled through a water body by gravitation or centrifugal force and which ends when they settle on a solid surface."" .

,Sedimentation in a water body is a type of material accumulation process that at least has parts of some precipitation process, occurs in some water body, involves some particulate environmental material as a participant, and concludes some material transport process. It is defined as a material accumulation process during which solid particles are pulled through a water body by gravitation or centrifugal force, and this process ends when they settle on a solid surface.",6,True
:has_definition ""An ablation zone which is part of a glacier.""

,The glacial ice ablation zone is a specific type of ice ablation zone that is part of at least some portion of a glacier and involves a process known as the glacial ice ablation process. It is defined as an ablation zone which is an integral part of a glacier. Additionally, this zone is exactly synonymous with the terms area of glacial ablation, glacial ablation area, and glacial ice ablation area.",7,True

:has_definition ""Particulate environmental material which is composed primarily of dust, rock, and soot, as well as the microbial communities associated with these materials, deposited on an ice mass by an aeolian process.""@en .

,Cryoconite deposit is a type of particulate environmental material, which is primarily composed of dust, rock, and soot, along with the microbial communities associated with these materials. It is deposited on an ice mass by an aeolian transport process. This means that a cryoconite deposit includes at least some parts of rock, dust, and soot, emphasizing its complex composition and origin.",6,True

:has_definition ""A vertical thaw hole within an ice mass, formed as a result of ice melt associated with local temperature increases, due to increased absorption of solar radiation by cryoconite deposits.""

,A cryoconite hole is a type of thaw hole and also a type of entity that at least has some part comprising cryoconite deposits. It is specifically defined as a vertical thaw hole within an ice mass, formed as a result of ice melt associated with local temperature increases, which occur due to the increased absorption of solar radiation by cryoconite deposits. Additionally, ""cryoconite holes"" is an exact synonym for cryoconite hole.",4,True

:has_definition ""A water body which forms as a result of localised melting taking place on the surface of a glacier or a mass of sea ice and which is contained in the cavity formed by such melting.""

,A melt pond is a type of water body characterized by several distinct features. It is a body of water that forms as a result of localized melting on the surface of a glacier or a mass of sea ice, contained within the cavity created by such melting. This process makes it at least partially comprised of meltwater and typically adjacent to some ice mass. Additionally, its formation is directly tied to the melting of ice. The term ""melt pond"" is precisely synonymous with ""melt ponds,"" ""meltpond,"" and ""meltponds.""",8,True

,A brine channel is a type of cryoform, channel, and something that at least has part some brine, is formed as a result of some brine channel formation process, and is composed primarily of some water ice. It is defined as a channel through which brine flows and is exactly synonymous with brine channels.",7,True
:has_definition ""A material accumulation process during which brine droplets, trapped between ice crystals formed during seawater freezing, form brine channels."" .

,The brine channel formation process is a type of liquid accumulation and hydrological process that at least precedes some brine rejection from seawater. This process involves brine and water ice as participants and results in the output of brine channels. It is defined as a material accumulation process during which brine droplets, trapped between ice crystals formed during seawater freezing, form brine channels.",7,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a portion of some environmental material is converted into a different material or a collection of materials."" .

,The material transformation process is a type of environmental system process and is also a type that requires at least some environmental material as input and produces some environmental material as output. It is defined as a process during which a portion of some environmental material is converted into a different material or a collection of materials.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000044,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which seawater freezes into sea ice."" .

,The sea ice formation process is a type of water ice formation process and is characterized as a material transformation process during which seawater freezes into sea ice. Moreover, this process is defined by at least having seawater as its input and producing sea ice as its output.",4,True
:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which brine is formed due to the expulsion of salt during frazil formation or a seawater freezing process."" .

,Brine rejection from seawater is a hydrological and material transformation process that is part of the sea ice formation process. It involves the input of seawater and results in the output of brine. Specifically, it is defined as a material transformation process during which brine is formed due to the expulsion of salt during frazil formation or a seawater freezing process.",6,True
:has_definition ""New ice which is composed frazil which has congealed into a thin sheet."" .

,Frazil ice is a type of new ice that is at least partially surrounded by some liquid water. It has qualities such as decreased size, being continuous, and laminar. Furthermore, frazil ice is primarily composed of frazil. It is defined as new ice which is composed of frazil that has congealed into a thin sheet.",7,True
:has_definition ""A new ice formation process during which small, needle-like crystals consisting of nearly pure fresh water, form due to the freezing of open, turbulent, supercooled water."" .

,Frazil ice formation is a type of new ice formation process and something that, at a minimum, results in the production of frazil ice. It is defined as a new ice formation process during which small, needle-like crystals consisting of nearly pure fresh water form due to the freezing of open, turbulent, supercooled water.",3,True
:has_definition ""A channel which traverses an ice mass floating on a water body and bridges the atmosphere to the underlying water through its internal cavity.""

,A thaw hole is a type of channel that is part of at least some ice floe and is formed as a result of icemelt. It is defined as a channel which traverses an ice mass floating on a water body and bridges the atmosphere to the underlying water through its internal cavity. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with thaw holes.",5,True
:has_definition ""A melt pond which has a surface exposed to the atmosphere."" .

,An atmosphere-exposed melt pond is defined as a melt pond that has a surface exposed to the atmosphere. It is a specific type of melt pond that is characterized by several key features. Firstly, it is identical to an entity that is at the intersection of a melt pond and an entity that, at the very least, includes a part that is at the intersection of surface water and an entity that is adjacent to the troposphere. Additionally, an atmosphere-exposed melt pond is classified under entities that have at least one part that is an intersection of surface water and something that is adjacent to the troposphere. It is also categorized as a type of entity that is adjacent to the troposphere and as a type of entity that is, at the very least, a result of some melting process.",6,True
:has_definition ""A melt pond which is completely encased in ice and thus not directly exposed to the atmosphere or underlying water."" .

,An ice-encased melt pond is a type of melt pond that is located in an ice mass and surrounded by water ice. It is the output of melting, indicating that its formation is a result of melting processes. The definition of an ice-encased melt pond is a melt pond which is completely encased in ice and thus not directly exposed to the atmosphere or underlying water.",5,True
:has_definition ""A lake which is comprised of meltwater located underneath or within a glacier.""

,An intraglacial lake is a type of lake that is characterized by being comprised of meltwater and is located underneath or within a glacier. This type of lake is not only defined as a lake which consists of meltwater located within a glacier but is also recognized by its exact synonym, intraglacial lakes.",5,True
:has_definition ""A process during which material entities are added to a landform or to a feature upon the landform."" .
,A depositional process is a type of material accumulation process, which is defined as a process during which material entities are added to a landform or to a feature upon the landform.",2,True
:has_definition ""A desublimation process during which water vapour is frozen into water ice."" .

,Desublimation of water vapour into ice is a type of desublimation process, a hydrological process, and something that at least has input some liquid water. It is defined as a desublimation process during which water vapour is frozen into water ice.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ice formation process during which water is frozen into a form of new ice such as frazil, grease ice, slush, or shuga."" .

,The new ice formation process is categorized under the water ice formation process. This process is recognized as a type that outputs an amalgamation that includes frazil ice, shuga, and slush ice. Furthermore, it is defined as an ice formation process where water freezes into new forms of ice, such as frazil, grease ice, slush, or shuga.",3,True
:has_definition ""A sea ice formation process during which new ice crystals freeze together, forming nilas, a thin, elastic, continuous, ice sheet of a transparent gray color."" .

,The Nilas formation process is a type of sea ice formation process that encompasses the input of some new ice and results in the output of some Nilas. It is defined as a sea ice formation process during which new ice crystals freeze together, forming Nilas, a thin, elastic, continuous ice sheet of a transparent gray color.",4,True
:has_definition ""A sea ice formation process during which water freezes to the bottom of an existing nilas ice floe creating a thicker ice floe known as young ice."" .

,The young ice formation process is a type of sea ice formation process that necessitates the intersection of sea water and nilas as inputs and results in the production of young ice as its output. It is defined as a sea ice formation process during which water freezes to the bottom of an existing nilas ice floe, thereby creating a thicker ice floe known as young ice.",4,True
:has_definition ""A sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes onto young ice during the cold season, forming first year ice."" .

,The first year ice formation process is a type of sea ice formation process that essentially involves the interaction between sea water and young ice, leading to the production of first year ice. This process is defined as a sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes onto young ice during the cold season, forming first year ice.",4,True
:has_definition ""A sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes onto first year ice during the cold season, forming second year sea ice."" .

,Second year ice formation is a type of sea ice formation process, which is characterized by having certain inputs and outputs. Specifically, it involves an input that includes the intersection of sea water and first year ice. The output of this process is second year ice. The definition of second year ice formation is a sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes onto first year ice during the cold season, resulting in the formation of second year sea ice.",4,True
:has_definition ""A sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes into second year ice during the cold season, forming multiyear ice."" .

,The multiyear ice formation process is a type of sea ice formation process that necessitates the intersection of seawater and second-year ice as inputs and results in the production of multiyear ice as an output. This process is defined as a sea ice formation process during which seawater freezes into second-year ice during the cold season, thereby forming multiyear ice.",4,True
:has_definition ""Water ice which is formed from freezing water and is suspended in a water body."" .

,New ice is a type of water ice, and it is also categorized as something that must be adjacent to some water body. Additionally, it is identified as something that is at least an output of a new ice formation process. The definition of new ice is water ice which is formed from freezing water and is suspended in a water body.",4,True
:has_definition ""An ice mass which forms a cohesive and contiguous sheet of water ice, floating upon the surface of a water body.""
,An ice floe is a type of ice mass characterized by several qualities
column2: it possesses some degree of continuity, buoyancy, and laminarity. Additionally, an ice floe is typically adjacent to some body of water. It is defined as an ice mass that forms a cohesive and contiguous sheet of water ice floating upon the surface of a water body. The term ""ice floes"" is an exact synonym for ice floe.",7,True

column1: :has_definition ""An ice floe which is formed from frozen sea water, and floats upon the surface of a marine water body.""

,A sea ice floe is a type of ice floe that is categorized by its proximity to at least one marine water body and its formation as a result of a sea ice formation process. :has_definition ""A sea ice floe which has a rounded or circular shape and raised rims."" .

,Pancake ice is a type of sea ice floe that has the quality of being somewhat circular. It is defined as a sea ice floe which has a rounded or circular shape and raised rims.,3,True

:has_definition ""A sea ice floe which is thin, elastic, continuous, and of a transparent gray color, which results from the freezing of new ice."" .

,Nilas is a type of sea ice floe characterized by being thin, elastic, continuous, and of a transparent gray color. This particular form of sea ice exhibits qualities of being at least somewhat transparent and somewhat elastic. It is formed as a result of a specific nilas formation process.
