:has_definition ""A sea ice floe which is inflexible and thicker than nilas."" .

,Young ice is a type of sea ice floe that is characterized by increased thickness and inflexibility. It is formed as a result of a young ice formation process. Moreover, young ice is defined as a sea ice floe which is inflexible and thicker than nilas.",5,True
:has_definition ""Sea ice which has formed over a single freezing season.""

,First year ice is a type of sea ice that has several characteristics. It is known for having an increased thickness and derives from young ice. Additionally, it is an output of the first year ice formation process. First year ice is defined as sea ice which has formed over a single freezing season and is also related to the synonym seasonal ice.",6,True
:has_definition ""Sea ice which is thicker than first year ice, and has survived a seasonal melting process."" .

,Second year ice is a type of sea ice characterized by increased thickness and the outcome of a second-year ice formation process. It is defined as sea ice that is thicker than first-year ice and has survived a seasonal melting process.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000073,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""Sea ice which is thicker than second year ice, and has survived more than two seasonal melting process."" .

,Multiyear ice is a type of sea ice characterized by its increased thickness and is the output of a multiyear ice formation process. It is defined as sea ice that is thicker than second-year ice and has survived more than two seasonal melting processes.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000074,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A layer which consists of a thin aggregate of frazil ice crystals, which float upon the surface of a water body."" .

,The grease ice layer is a type of water ice layer, which is characterized by its decreased thickness and adjacency to a water body. It is defined as a layer consisting of a thin aggregate of frazil ice crystals that float upon the surface of a water body.",4,True
:has_definition ""New ice, which is spongy, lumpy and opaque, and forms from water which freezes in an agitated water body."" .

,Shuga is a type of new ice and something that at least has some opaque quality. It is defined as new ice which is spongy, lumpy, and opaque, forming from water that freezes in an agitated water body.",3,True
:has_definition ""A slurry of frazil, snow, and liquid water."" .

,Slush ice is the same as something that intersects with environmental material and something that, at the very least, has a part of something that is an intersection of liquid water, snow, and frazil ice. Additionally, slush ice is identified as a type of environmental material and also as a type that must include parts of something that intersects with liquid water, snow, and frazil ice. Furthermore, slush ice is defined as a slurry comprising frazil, snow, and liquid water.",4,True
:has_definition ""A layer which consists of slush ice."" .

,A slush ice layer is a type of water ice layer that is at least adjacent to some water body and is composed primarily of slush ice. It is defined as a layer which consists of slush ice.,4,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000078,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A new ice formation process in which slush ice is formed."" .

,The slush formation process is a new ice formation process characterized by the formation of slush ice. It requires inputs that include a combination of liquid water, snow, and frazil ice. The output of this process is slush ice. Essentially, the slush formation process is defined as a new ice formation process where slush ice is produced.",4,True
:has_definition ""A new ice formation process in which shuga is formed."" .

,The shuga formation process is a type of new ice formation process and is defined as a new ice formation process in which shuga is formed. This process is characterized by something that at least outputs some shuga.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000082,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A freshwater lake which fills a depression formed by the erosion of thermokarst caused by permafrost thaw.""

,A thermokarst lake is a type of freshwater lake, which is essentially a part of thermokarst and is adjacent to a thermokarst depression. It is formed as a result of the thawing process of ice-bearing permafrost and is primarily composed of meltwater. The term is defined as a freshwater lake that fills a depression formed by the erosion of thermokarst caused by permafrost thaw. Furthermore, thermokarst lake is exactly synonymous with cave-in lake, thaw lake, and thermokarst lakes.",9,True
:has_definition ""A thermokarst lake through which methane gas released from thawing permafrost, or other methane stores, rises and escapes to the atmosphere."" .

,A methane releasing thermokarst lake is a type of thermokarst lake that participates in methane gas emission processes and possesses the quality of being blue. It is also characterized by being adjacent to the atmosphere. The definition of a methane releasing thermokarst lake is a thermokarst lake through which methane gas, released from thawing permafrost or other methane stores, rises and escapes to the atmosphere.",5,True
:has_definition ""A geographic basin which is formed due to the erosion of thermokarst by meltwater released from thawing permafrost."" .

,Thermokarst depression is a type of geographic basin and part of a landmass, characterized as being at least partially comprised of some thermokarst and formed as a result of ice-bearing permafrost thawing processes. It is defined as a geographic basin formed due to the erosion of thermokarst by meltwater released from thawing permafrost.",5,True
:has_definition ""An irregular land surface which consists of marshy hollows, hummocks, thermokarst depressions and thermokarst lakes formed from the erosion of ice-rich thawing permafrost areas."" .

,Thermokarst is a type of planetary landmass characterized by an irregular land surface consisting of marshy hollows, hummocks, thermokarst depressions, and thermokarst lakes. This formation results from the erosion of ice-rich thawing permafrost areas. Furthermore, thermokarst is described as something that includes at least a part of thermokarst depression and is formed as a result of the thawing process of ice-bearing permafrost.",4,True
:has_definition ""A permafrost thawing process during which water-based ice or snow present in permafrost is converted into meltwater."" .

,The ice bearing permafrost thawing process is a multifaceted phenomenon, classified under several categories due to its complex nature. Primarily, it is recognized as a type of permafrost thawing process. Additionally, it plays a significant role in the warming of both liquids and solids, highlighting its impact on different states of matter. This process is also categorized under hydrological processes, emphasizing its involvement in water-related changes in the environment. More specifically, it is part of processes that inherently include hydrological melting processes, indicating its critical contribution to the transformation of ice to water.

Furthermore, the ice bearing permafrost thawing process is intricately linked to water ice and permafrost, as it involves the interaction with substances that are both part of permafrost and contain water ice. One of the key outcomes of this process is the production of meltwater, showcasing its role in the conversion of solid ice within permafrost into liquid water. Moreover, this process is causally upstream of methane gas emission processes, indicating its indirect contribution to the release of methane into the atmosphere, a potent greenhouse gas.

The ice bearing permafrost thawing process is comprehensively defined as a permafrost thawing process during which water-based ice or snow present in permafrost is converted into meltwater. This definition encapsulates the essence of the process, illustrating its critical role in the transformation of permafrost and its implications for the environment.",9,True
:has_definition ""Permafrost which contains pockets of trapped methane gas.""

,Methane-laden permafrost is defined as permafrost which contains pockets of trapped methane gas, and it is synonymous with bulgunyakh. This type of permafrost is both a kind of permafrost and a kind that has at least some part methane. Additionally, methane-laden permafrost is equivalent to the intersection of permafrost and anything that has at least a part of methane.",5,True
:has_definition ""A crater which is found in permafrost and formed as a result of an explosion fuelled by methane formerly contained in that permafrost."" .

,A permafrost crater derived from a methane explosion, which can also be broadly referred to as a gigantic funnel, is a type of crater. It is specifically defined as a crater found in permafrost that formed as a result of an explosion fueled by methane previously contained in that permafrost. This indicates that such a crater is at least formed as a result of some permafrost methane explosion.",4,True
:has_definition ""A process during which a material entity undergoes a rapid increase in volume, releasing gasses and various forms of energy, often including thermal, light and sound energy.""

,An explosion process is a type of combustion process that involves materials which are at the intersection of a chemical entity and an oxidising agent, as well as materials at the intersection of environmental material and fuel, as inputs. It results in the output of gaseous environmental material. This process is defined as a process during which a material entity undergoes a rapid increase in volume, releasing gases and various forms of energy, often including thermal, light, and sound energy. The explosion process is also exactly synonymous with the term ""explosion.""",6,True
:has_definition ""An explosion during which methane-rich gas trapped in permafrost combusts."" .

,A permafrost methane explosion is a type of explosion process that occurs in some permafrost areas and involves several participants including dioxygen, permafrost itself, and a gaseous environmental material primarily composed of methane. This specific explosion process is defined as an explosion during which methane-rich gas trapped in permafrost combusts.",6,True
:has_definition ""A material transport process during which a portion of gaseous environmental material is transported into the atmosphere."" .

,The gas emission process is described as a type of material transport process, which has a specific relationship with elements that involve gaseous environmental materials. It is characterized by having an input that includes elements which are an intersection of gaseous environmental material and entities not entirely part of the atmosphere. Similarly, its output involves elements that are at the intersection of gaseous environmental material and entities that are at least partially part of the atmosphere. Moreover, the gas emission process is defined as a material transport process during which a portion of the gaseous environmental material is transported into the atmosphere.",4,True
:has_definition ""A gas emission process during which a portion of hydrocarbon gas is transported into the atmosphere."" .

,The hydrocarbon gas emission process is a specific type of gas emission process characterized by the transportation of a portion of hydrocarbon gas into the atmosphere, as defined. This process involves at least one participant, which is some hydrocarbon gas, and is causally upstream of, or contributes to, the greenhouse effect.",4,True
:has_definition ""A hydrocarbon gas emission process during which a portion of methane gas is transported into the atmosphere."" .

,The methane gas emission process is a type of hydrocarbon gas emission process and is also a type of process that at least has methane as a participant. It is defined as a hydrocarbon gas emission process during which a portion of methane gas is transported into the atmosphere.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000095,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .

:has_definition ""A process during which the intesity of stellar radiation received by a planet's surface varies in a cyclical regime due to the planet's orbital motion around the barycentre of a planetary system and/or the tilt of its rotational axis relative to its orbital plane."" .

,The season generating process is characterized as a type of environmental system process that involves at least one planet and one star as participants. Furthermore, it is described as being causally upstream of or within a season. The definition of a season generating process is a process during which the intensity of stellar radiation received by a planet's surface varies in a cyclical regime due to the planet's orbital motion around the barycentre of a planetary system and/or the tilt of its rotational axis relative to its orbital plane.",5,True
:has_definition ""A one-dimensional temporal region which is delimited by the occurrence of processes which serve as its delimiters."" .
,A season is a type of one-dimensional temporal region, defined as a one-dimensional temporal region that is delimited by the occurrence of processes which serve as its delimiters.",2,True
:has_definition ""A season during which the average temperature of a planetary part exceeds that of all other seasons it endures during a season generating process."" .

,The warm season is a type of season defined as a period during which the average temperature of a planetary part exceeds that of all other seasons it endures during a season-generating process.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000098,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""A season during which the average temperature of a planetary part is below that of all other seasons it endures during a season generating process."" .

,Cold season is a type of season that is defined as a season during which the average temperature of a planetary part is below that of all other seasons it endures during a season-generating process.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000099,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A material transformation process during which a material entity melts during a warm season."" .

,The seasonal melting process is a type of melting that specifically begins during a warm season. It is defined as a material transformation process during which a material entity melts during a warm season.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000101,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A compaction process during which a material entity subjected to heat and/or pressure is compacted into a solid mass without undergoing melting."" .

,Solid phase sintering is a type of compaction process, and it is also a type of something that requires input from materials that are both environmental and porous. It is defined as a compaction process during which a material entity, subjected to heat and/or pressure, is compacted into a solid mass without undergoing melting.",3,True
:has_definition ""A sintering process during which snow is compacted into glacial ice."" .

,Glacial sintering is a type of hydrological process and a type of solid phase sintering. It is a process that takes in some amount of snow and outputs some glacial ice. Additionally, glacial sintering is defined as a sintering process during which snow is compacted into glacial ice.",5,True
:has_definition ""An aeolian transport process during which powdery snow is displaced and moved."" .

,Aeolian transport of snow is a type of aeolian transport process and is also a type of process that requires at least some powdery snow as input. It is defined as an aeolian transport process during which powdery snow is displaced and moved.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000104,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An accumulation process during which a powdery snow carried on the wind settles on a solid surface, forming a mound.""

,Snow drift formation is a type of snow accumulation process and an exact synonym for it is the drifting of unsintered snow. This process involves powdery snow as a participant and ends the aeolian transport of snow. Specifically, snow drift formation is defined as an accumulation process during which powdery snow carried on the wind settles on a solid surface, forming a mound.",5,True
:has_definition ""A mass wasting process during which slab snow rapidly moves down a sloping surface."" .
,A slab avalanche is a type of mass wasting, which is defined as a mass wasting process during which slab snow rapidly moves down a sloping surface.",2,True
:has_definition ""An avalanche during which powdery snow rapidly flows down a sloping surface.""

,A powdery snow avalanche, which is also exactly known as a powder snow avalanche, is a type of avalanche. It is characterized as an event during which powdery snow rapidly flows down a sloping surface. This type of avalanche involves participants that are an intersection of materials found in the environment and entities that are at least primarily composed of powdery snow.",4,True
:has_definition ""An avalanche during which a suspension of water and snow flows down a sloping surface."" .

,A wet snow avalanche is a type of avalanche and also a type of water flow process. It involves participants that are at the intersection of environmental material and liquid water, and it is primarily composed of snow. Moreover, a wet snow avalanche is defined as an avalanche during which a suspension of water and snow flows down a sloping surface.",4,True
:has_definition ""Snow which is cohesive, hard and overlies weaker snow."" .
,Slab snow is a type of snow that is defined as snow which is cohesive, hard, and overlies weaker snow.",2,True
:has_definition ""A solid astronomical body part which is primarily composed of a continuous mass of snow and/or ice."" .

,Cryoform is equivalent to an entity that is both a solid astronomical body part and primarily composed of a combination of permafrost, water ice, and snow. As a type, cryoform falls under the category of solid astronomical body parts and is characterized by its primary composition, which includes any of the following: permafrost, water ice, or snow. Additionally, cryoform is defined as a solid astronomical body part that is mainly made up of a continuous mass of snow and/or ice.",4,True

,Snow mass is equivalent to an intersection of objects that are masses of compounded environmental materials and those that are at least composed primarily of snow. It is a type of mass of compounded environmental materials and also a type of entity that is at least formed as a result of some snow accumulation process. Furthermore, snow mass is a type of entity that is at least composed primarily of snow. It is defined as a mass of snow and has broad synonyms including accumulation of snow and snow accumulation.",7,True
:has_definition ""An accumulation of powdery snow which was transported and deposited via a snow drifting process.""

,Snow drift is a type of snow mass that is at least formed as a result of snow drift formation and is at least composed primarily of powdery snow. It is defined as an accumulation of powdery snow which was transported and deposited via a snow drifting process. Additionally, snow drift has exact synonyms, including snowdrift and unsintered snow.",6,True
:has_definition ""An accumulation of snow and firn which rests upon land.""

,A snow patch is a type of snow mass that is adjacent to some planetary landmass and formed as a result of some cold season. It is primarily composed of something that is an intersection of snow and firn. Moreover, a snow patch is defined as an accumulation of snow and firn which rests upon land and has an exact synonym, snowpatch.",6,True
:has_definition ""A snow patch which forms during a cold season and melts away during the succeeding warm season.""

,A seasonal snow patch is a type of snow patch that participates in a seasonal melting process, forming during a cold season and melting away during the succeeding warm season. It is defined as a snow patch which forms during a cold season and melts away during the succeeding warm season. Additionally, ""seasonal snowpatch"" is an exact synonym for a seasonal snow patch.",4,True
:has_definition ""A snow patch which persists through at least one seasonal cycle.""

,A perennial snow patch is a type of snow patch and also a type of entity that participates in some seasonal melting process. It is defined as a snow patch which persists through at least one seasonal cycle. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: perennial snowpatch.",4,True
:has_definition ""A snow mass which is large enough, and persists long enough, to undergo compaction under its own weight, leading to layer-like structural differentiation.""@en

,Snowpack is a type of snow mass that at least participates in some compaction process. It is defined as a snow mass which is large enough, and persists long enough, to undergo compaction under its own weight, leading to layer-like structural differentiation. Additionally, snowpack has an exact synonym: snow pack.",4,True
:has_definition ""A structure which traverses a mass of one or more environmental materials, and encloses a roughly tubular site."" .

,A channel is a type of landform and also a type of something that has at least some tubular quality. It is defined as a structure which traverses a mass of one or more environmental materials and encloses a roughly tubular site.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000118,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A melt pond which and is exposed to the atmosphere and to a lesser degree water underlying the ice mass which contains it.""

,An atmosphere and water column exposed melt pond is a type of melt pond that is also classified as something adjacent to at least some part of the troposphere. It is defined as a melt pond that is exposed to the atmosphere and, to a lesser degree, to the underlying water beneath the ice mass that contains it. Additionally, this type of melt pond is exactly synonymous with the term ""open melt pond.""",4,True
:has_definition ""A melt pond which is formed close to that part of an ice mass which is in contact with some underlying water body, and which has channels connecting it to that water body."" .

,A water column exposed melt pond is a type of melt pond defined as a melt pond formed close to the part of an ice mass in contact with an underlying water body, featuring channels connecting it to that water body.",2,True
:has_definition ""A lake which is situated beneath a glacier.""

,A subglacial lake is a type of ice-covered lake, which is, by definition, a lake situated beneath a glacier. It is also a type of entity that is at least adjacent to some glacier and some planetary landmass. Furthermore, ""subglacial lakes"" is an exact synonym for subglacial lake.",5,True
:has_definition ""An erosion process during which rock or soil is removed or degraded due to alternative thawing and freezing of meltwater beneath and at the margins of snowbanks."" .

,Erosion through nivation is a type of planetary erosion and also a type of erosion that involves the union of various processes, specifically the intersection of activities involving soil and those that at least involve some aspect of soil erosion, as well as processes that at least have rocks as participants. Additionally, erosion through nivation is characterized by having nivation as an integral part of its process. The definition of erosion through nivation is an erosion process during which rock or soil is removed or degraded due to the alternative thawing and freezing of meltwater beneath and at the margins of snowbanks.",4,True
:has_definition ""A fire which is planned and executed deliberately under human supervision.""
,A planned burn is a type of fire that is defined as a fire which is planned and executed deliberately under human supervision. Moreover, it has a narrow synonym known as fire-stick farming.",3,True
:has_definition ""The concentration of nitrate and nitrite when measured in liquid water.""

,The concentration of nitrate and nitrite in liquid water is defined as the concentration of nitrate and nitrite when measured in liquid water. It is a type of concentration and has the exact synonym ""liquid water nitrate and nitrite concentration."" This concentration is the same as something that encompasses both the concentration of nitrate in liquid water and the concentration of nitrite in liquid water.",4,True
:has_definition ""A water-based rainfall process during which water droplets with increased acidity fall towards a planetary surface."" .

,Acid rainfall is a type of water-based rainfall, water flow process, and something that has at least some acidic water as a participant. It is defined as a water-based rainfall process during which water droplets with increased acidity fall towards a planetary surface. Additionally, acid rainfall is broadly synonymous with acid rain.",5,True

,Acidic water-based rain is a type of water-based rain and is also known as acid rain. It is a type of phenomenon that participates in acid rainfall and has the quality of being acidic. Acidic water-based rain is defined as water-based rain which has increased acidity.,5,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000129,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:has_definition ""A season during which changes in atmospheric circulation associated with the asymmetric heating of land and sea cause moisture to be brought inland by monsoon winds, leading to increased rainfall as moisture-laden air rises  and cools over land."" .

,The monsoon season is a type of season that is defined as a period during which changes in atmospheric circulation, associated with the asymmetric heating of land and sea, cause moisture to be brought inland by monsoon winds. This leads to increased rainfall as moisture-laden air rises and cools over land.",2,True
:has_definition ""An atmospheric wind during which air masses over an ocean flow towards a land mass, driven by disequilibria between land and ocean surface temperatures."" .

,Monsoon wind is a type of atmospheric wind that plays a significant role in the interaction between marine water bodies and planetary landmasses. It is characterized by a specific season, known as the monsoon season, during which these interactions are particularly pronounced. The definition of monsoon wind elaborates on this interaction: an atmospheric wind during which air masses over an ocean flow towards a landmass, driven by disequilibria between land and ocean surface temperatures.",5,True
:has_definition ""A fire which occurs in a grassland, combusting biomass stored in grasses as its primary fuel."" .

,Grass fire is a type of land fire and also a type of event that occurs in some grassland area. It is defined as a fire which occurs in a grassland, combusting biomass stored in grasses as its primary fuel.",3,True
:has_definition ""A woodland clearing which is large enough to starve land fires of fuel, impeding their progress through wooded areas.""

,Firebreak, also known as fire break, is a type of woodland clearing that is significantly involved in the negative regulation of land fires. It is defined as a large woodland clearing sufficient to starve land fires of fuel, thereby impeding their progress through wooded areas.",4,True

:has_definition ""An agricultural environmental material which 1) is composed of a mixture of materials such as peat, composted bark, sand, perlite, or compost, and 2) serves as a medium in which to grow plants.""@en

,An agricultural potting mixture is a type of agricultural environmental material, which is defined as an agricultural environmental material composed of a mixture of materials such as peat, composted bark, sand, perlite, or compost. This mixture serves as a medium in which to grow plants. Additionally, agricultural potting mixture is exactly synonymous with potting soil.",3,True
:has_definition ""A blizzard which 1) lasts at least 3 hours, 2) combines below freezing temperatures and very strong wind, laden with blowing snow.""@en .

,A WMO blizzard is a type of blizzard defined by the World Meteorological Organization as a blizzard which 1) lasts at least 3 hours, 2) combines below freezing temperatures and very strong wind, laden with blowing snow.",2,True

:has_definition ""A blizzard which has 1) winds of 35 miles per hour (approximately 56 kilometers per hour), 2) lasts for a period of at least three hours, and 3) occurs in extremely cold temperatures.""@en .

,An NSIDC blizzard is a specific type of blizzard characterized by having winds of 35 miles per hour (approximately 56 kilometers per hour), lasting for a period of at least three hours, and occurring in extremely cold temperatures.",2,True

,A winter blizzard is a type of blizzard that is defined as a blizzard which occurs in winter.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000137,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""A fog the droplets of which freeze upon contact with exposed objects, forming a coating of rime or glaze.""@en .

,Freezing fog is a type of fog and a type of phenomenon that is at least capable of an intersection process involving water ice formation and at least has an output that is a union of either a glaze ice layer or rime. It is defined as a fog whose droplets freeze upon contact with exposed objects, forming a coating of rime or glaze.",3,True

:has_definition ""A particle which is 1) primarily compposed of water ice, 2) on the order of 1 milimeter or less, 3) has a white and opaque appearance, and 4) is formed as a result of water droplets freezing during precipitation.""@en

,A particle of snow is a type of ice mass, particle, and something that is at least part of some snow or derives from part of some snow. It is also a type of something that at least has the quality of being both white and opaque, and it is a member of something that is both an object aggregate and at least part of some snow. Additionally, a particle of snow is a type of something that is at least formed as a result of the freezing of water into water ice. The definition of a particle of snow is a particle which is primarily composed of water ice, on the order of 1 millimeter or less, has a white and opaque appearance, and is formed as a result of water droplets freezing during precipitation. It has exact synonyms including grain of snow, granule of snow, snow grain, snow granule, and snow particle. Moreover, it has a related synonym, which is granular snow.",13,True
:has_definition ""Fog which is composed of particles of ice.""@en

,Ice fog is a type of fog, aerosolised solids, and something that is at least composed primarily of water ice. It is defined as fog which is composed of particles of ice. Ice fog is exactly synonymous with frozen fog, ice-crystal fog, and pogonip. Additionally, it has related synonyms such as air hoar, frost flakes, frost fog, and rime fog.",11,True

:has_definition ""A climate which 1) has a mean temperature for the warmest month of less than 10°C (50°F), but higher than 0°C (32°F), 2) is not conducive to a permanent surficial cover of snow or ice, and 3) supports a tundra ecosystem.""@en .

,Tundra climate is a type of climate defined by several characteristics: it has a mean temperature for the warmest month of less than 10°C (50°F) but higher than 0°C (32°F), it is not conducive to a permanent surficial cover of snow or ice, and it supports a tundra ecosystem.",2,True
:has_definition ""A cryospheric layer which is primarily composed of snow.""@en

,A snow layer is a type of cryospheric layer, which is something that is at least composed primarily of snow. It is defined as a cryospheric layer primarily composed of snow. Additionally, ""snow cover"" is a related synonym to snow layer.",4,True
:has_definition ""A depth which inheres in a layer of liquid water derived from the complete melting a mass of snow contained in an area.""@en .

,Snow water equivalent is a type of depth defined as the depth which inheres in a layer of liquid water derived from the complete melting of a mass of snow contained in an area.,2,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000143,@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
:has_definition ""An astronomical body part which is composed primarily of environmental materials in their frozen form.""@en .

,The cryosphere is a type of astronomical body part that is primarily composed of environmental materials in their frozen form. Additionally, it can be described as something that intersects with environmental material and has the quality of being frozen. The cryosphere is defined as an astronomical body part which is composed primarily of environmental materials in their frozen form.",3,True
:has_definition ""A cryosphere which is part of a planet.""@en .

,The planetary cryosphere is a type of cryosphere and is defined as a cryosphere that is part of a planet. It is also characterized as a type of entity that constitutes at least part of some planet.,3,True
envo,http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000145,@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
:has_definition ""An environmental zone which is covered or partially covered by snow.""@en .
,The area of snow cover is a type of environmental zone, defined as an environmental zone which is covered or partially covered by snow.",2,True

:has_definition ""A material transport process during which liquid water is circulated in the vicinity of a heat source in order to absorb thermal energy and transport it away form that source.""@en .

,The thickness of snow, which is a type of thickness and also a type of characteristic that at least some snow possesses, is equivalent to something that intersects with something having thickness and something that at least has a characteristic of some snow.
